1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:16,449
It's finally game day.

2
00:00:16,516 --> 00:00:19,185
Today, we are here to present

3
00:00:19,252 --> 00:00:22,322
the 2025 <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> Championship.

4
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:26,092
-Tension is high in the studio.
-Yes.

5
00:00:26,159 --> 00:00:27,127
THE AIR IS DIFFERENT

6
00:00:27,193 --> 00:00:30,997
I mean, this is just for entertainment,
but you all seem quite concerned.

7
00:00:31,064 --> 00:00:34,034
It may be just for entertainment,
but as chefs, shouldn't we do our best?

8
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:35,135
SAYS POONG WITH CONFIDENCE

9
00:00:35,201 --> 00:00:36,269
"As chefs"?

10
00:00:36,336 --> 00:00:37,737
-Can someone else say it?
-Right?

11
00:00:37,804 --> 00:00:40,573
-No one would say it.
-I see.

12
00:00:40,640 --> 00:00:42,742
Chef Hyun-suk, you look like a scholar.

13
00:00:43,443 --> 00:00:45,078
-I finally…
-Scholar Choi.

14
00:00:45,145 --> 00:00:47,147
…began to see the world clearly.

15
00:00:47,914 --> 00:00:50,150
-So you admit to looking at it crookedly?
-Also,

16
00:00:50,216 --> 00:00:51,551
-I wanted to focus on cooking.
-He did.

17
00:00:51,618 --> 00:00:53,820
Are you saying
you were never focused until today?

18
00:00:53,887 --> 00:00:55,055
Are those reading glasses?

19
00:00:55,121 --> 00:00:56,723
-We haven't even started.
-I was focused.

20
00:00:56,790 --> 00:00:58,124
He became old and farsighted.

21
00:00:58,191 --> 00:00:59,092
Farsightedness.

22
00:00:59,159 --> 00:01:01,161
-I can hear you.
-You heard me?

23
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:05,031
Only the top five chefs
of the regular league

24
00:01:05,098 --> 00:01:09,269
are allowed to participate
in the championship playoffs.

25
00:01:09,335 --> 00:01:11,638
Why don't we present the faces of glory?

26
00:01:11,704 --> 00:01:12,772
<i>In fifth place,</i>

27
00:01:14,507 --> 00:01:16,643
<i>-we have Chef Son Jong-won.</i>
<i>-Chef Jong-won takes fifth place.</i>

28
00:01:16,709 --> 00:01:17,811
<i>Fourth place.</i>

29
00:01:17,877 --> 00:01:19,045
<i>-Chef Park Eun-yeong.</i>
<i>-Chef Eun-yeong.</i>

30
00:01:20,213 --> 00:01:21,481
<i>Third place.</i>

31
00:01:21,548 --> 00:01:22,549
<i>Webtoon Artist Kim Poong.</i>

32
00:01:23,783 --> 00:01:24,617
<i>Second place.</i>

33
00:01:25,318 --> 00:01:26,252
<i>Chef Jung Ho-young.</i>

34
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:28,855
<i>Lastly, the top, first place.</i>

35
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:30,223
<i>Chef Choi Hyun-suk.</i>

36
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:32,092
Chef Choi Hyun-suk.

37
00:01:32,158 --> 00:01:34,027
I'M THE CHEF IN 1ST PLACE

38
00:01:34,094 --> 00:01:37,831
Choi Hyun-suk secures first place
after the regular league.

39
00:01:37,897 --> 00:01:38,998
Yes.

40
00:01:39,065 --> 00:01:41,801
The winner of the championship,

41
00:01:41,868 --> 00:01:44,304
namely, the best chef of <i>Chef & My Fridge,</i>

42
00:01:44,370 --> 00:01:45,405
-gets something, right?
-Yes.

43
00:01:45,472 --> 00:01:46,306
Why don't we show them?

44
00:01:46,372 --> 00:01:47,540
-Let me bring it out.
-Must be something nice.

45
00:01:47,607 --> 00:01:48,875
-Do we get a fridge?
-It's amazing.

46
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:50,076
We get a fridge?

47
00:01:50,143 --> 00:01:52,045
-This is heavy.
-What's that?

48
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:53,613
This is the present for the best chef.

49
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:55,048
Let me show you.

50
00:01:55,615 --> 00:01:58,184
AMAZED

51
00:01:58,251 --> 00:01:59,252
Let me show you.

52
00:01:59,319 --> 00:02:00,920
TA-DA

53
00:02:00,987 --> 00:02:03,022
CHEF & MY FRIDGE

54
00:02:04,257 --> 00:02:06,292
This is a one-of-a-kind trophy.

55
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:07,260
Only for one person.

56
00:02:07,327 --> 00:02:08,728
That's different.

57
00:02:08,795 --> 00:02:10,163
It's fancy.

58
00:02:10,230 --> 00:02:12,198
It'll look perfect
by your restaurant's entrance.

59
00:02:12,265 --> 00:02:13,833
-It's for our business.
-Yes.

60
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,335
<i>Culinary Class Wars</i> didn't have this.

61
00:02:15,969 --> 00:02:18,004
-Sam doesn't even get a chance today.
-No.

62
00:02:18,238 --> 00:02:19,105
DIDN'T MAKE THE CUT

63
00:02:19,172 --> 00:02:20,573
May I just take a picture later?

64
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:22,709
YOU'RE MORE THAN WELCOME TO

65
00:02:22,775 --> 00:02:24,911
<i>Take your pictures</i>
<i>before the rightful owner is decided.</i>

66
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:26,613
Please don't take this the wrong way.

67
00:02:26,679 --> 00:02:28,615
This isn't the end of our show.

68
00:02:28,681 --> 00:02:31,050
-It's the year-end playoff.
-Just for the year 2025.

69
00:02:31,117 --> 00:02:32,585
Who's going to take the trophy

70
00:02:32,652 --> 00:02:34,888
for <i>Chef & My Fridge </i>Championship?

71
00:02:34,954 --> 00:02:37,223
And because this is a special occasion,

72
00:02:37,290 --> 00:02:42,128
two special guests came to visit,
the celebrities who thrived in 2025.

73
00:02:42,195 --> 00:02:45,031
Please welcome today's fridge owners!

74
00:02:45,098 --> 00:02:46,466
Come on out!

75
00:02:46,533 --> 00:02:47,867
-Who are they?
-This is awesome!

76
00:02:47,934 --> 00:02:49,802
Today's fridge owners!

77
00:02:50,370 --> 00:02:51,304
WHOA

78
00:02:51,371 --> 00:02:53,306
Today's fridge owners!

79
00:02:53,373 --> 00:02:55,675
The two variety show champions of 2025,

80
00:02:55,742 --> 00:02:58,011
Kim Won-hun and Lee Su-ji!

81
00:02:58,077 --> 00:03:00,046
-Hello.
-It's great to have you.

82
00:03:00,113 --> 00:03:01,314
You're the first of your kind.

83
00:03:01,381 --> 00:03:04,317
<i>He took over YouTube and variety shows</i>

84
00:03:04,384 --> 00:03:05,818
<i>as the hottest of the hottest.</i>

85
00:03:05,885 --> 00:03:08,288
-In or out?
-In or out?

86
00:03:08,354 --> 00:03:09,889
I mean, it's kind of iffy
to gamble all our money away.

87
00:03:09,956 --> 00:03:11,991
In 2025, "I mean,

88
00:03:12,058 --> 00:03:13,092
I am the trend."

89
00:03:13,159 --> 00:03:15,061
Please welcome Comedian Kim Won-hun!

90
00:03:15,128 --> 00:03:15,962
COMEDIAN KIM WON-HUN

91
00:03:16,396 --> 00:03:17,230
WELCOME, IN OR OUT?

92
00:03:17,297 --> 00:03:19,032
Hello.

93
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:21,334
Wait, Sung-ju.

94
00:03:21,401 --> 00:03:23,336
I guess you don't watch my YouTube videos.

95
00:03:23,403 --> 00:03:24,270
What do you mean?

96
00:03:24,337 --> 00:03:27,373
That's not how I say "I mean."

97
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:29,442
-No? But I watched a lot of your videos.
-No.

98
00:03:29,509 --> 00:03:31,411
-No.
-How do I do it?

99
00:03:31,477 --> 00:03:32,845
I mean, I am the trend.

100
00:03:33,179 --> 00:03:34,214
SO GOOD

101
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:35,715
"I mean, I am the trend."

102
00:03:35,782 --> 00:03:38,084
-You're hilarious. All right.
-Thank you.

103
00:03:38,151 --> 00:03:39,419
Please introduce the next guest.

104
00:03:39,485 --> 00:03:40,720
I'm personally a fan.

105
00:03:40,787 --> 00:03:42,922
My gosh. Me too.

106
00:03:42,989 --> 00:03:44,724
Jung-hwan rarely ever says this.

107
00:03:44,791 --> 00:03:46,092
<i>The woman of a thousand faces!</i>

108
00:03:46,159 --> 00:03:49,295
<i>She was the hottest issue in 2025!</i>

109
00:03:49,362 --> 00:03:51,097
Please welcome Comedian Lee Su-ji!

110
00:03:51,731 --> 00:03:52,899
-Hello.
-Welcome!

111
00:03:53,199 --> 00:03:56,369
IT'S GREAT TO HAVE YOU

112
00:03:56,436 --> 00:03:58,238
There's a reason why they came together.

113
00:03:58,304 --> 00:03:59,739
Su-ji said

114
00:03:59,806 --> 00:04:02,842
she wanted to come to <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>
with Won-hun.

115
00:04:02,909 --> 00:04:05,245
I heard you shared that with us.

116
00:04:05,311 --> 00:04:07,013
I didn't emphasize it that much.

117
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:09,115
-You didn't?
-No, I didn't.

118
00:04:09,182 --> 00:04:11,584
-I just recommended you.
-It was a recommendation?

119
00:04:11,651 --> 00:04:14,954
Won-hun and I worked together
in many different programs,

120
00:04:15,021 --> 00:04:16,856
-so we often had team dinners.
-Right.

121
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:19,692
And every single place he recommended
was delicious.

122
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:21,494
REALLY?

123
00:04:21,561 --> 00:04:22,662
He knows what's good.

124
00:04:22,729 --> 00:04:26,432
I already knew she'd enjoy
everything I recommended

125
00:04:26,499 --> 00:04:27,867
because she finds everything good.

126
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:29,702
HAHA

127
00:04:29,769 --> 00:04:32,538
She enjoys everything a lot,
so it's nice to see that.

128
00:04:32,605 --> 00:04:35,475
-I hear Won-hun has a special talent.
-What is it?

129
00:04:35,541 --> 00:04:37,110
He can take a look at Su-ji's face

130
00:04:37,176 --> 00:04:39,178
-and guess what she ate.
-Really?

131
00:04:39,245 --> 00:04:40,380
That's his talent.

132
00:04:40,446 --> 00:04:42,649
Whenever we meet,

133
00:04:42,715 --> 00:04:45,385
I often see some lettuce
stuck in her teeth.

134
00:04:45,785 --> 00:04:46,819
DYING

135
00:04:46,886 --> 00:04:48,254
Don't archaeologists

136
00:04:48,321 --> 00:04:51,991
-excavate and find these things to see…
-Archaeologists?

137
00:04:52,058 --> 00:04:54,460
…that people ate things like bracken
back then?

138
00:04:54,527 --> 00:04:55,962
That's how I usually take a guess.

139
00:04:56,029 --> 00:04:58,898
I once said goodbye to her,
shook her hand, and turned around,

140
00:04:58,965 --> 00:05:02,735
and realized I had
a whole lot of hand cream on my hands.

141
00:05:02,802 --> 00:05:04,637
So I smelled it,
and it smelled like pig trotters.

142
00:05:05,071 --> 00:05:06,939
CHECKING HER MEAL VIA SMELL

143
00:05:07,006 --> 00:05:08,808
-I like finger food.
-Collagen.

144
00:05:08,875 --> 00:05:11,277
-For collagen.
-I like to eat with my hand.

145
00:05:11,344 --> 00:05:14,414
And when she eats,
I guess the food splatters on her.

146
00:05:14,647 --> 00:05:15,815
THE EPISODES DON'T END

147
00:05:15,882 --> 00:05:18,551
One time, I saw her
after she had eaten <i>bibim naengmyeon,</i>

148
00:05:18,618 --> 00:05:20,353
and I thought she had a skin condition

149
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:23,323
because she had red specks everywhere,
even behind her neck.

150
00:05:23,389 --> 00:05:25,258
He asked if I had an allergic reaction.

151
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:26,859
It was on your ankle bone too.

152
00:05:26,926 --> 00:05:27,894
Oh, come on.

153
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:30,063
-I don't eat like this!
-Ankle bone?

154
00:05:30,129 --> 00:05:33,333
-I saw the spicy sauce on her ankle bone.
-Stop lying.

155
00:05:33,399 --> 00:05:35,768
-It means she enjoys her food.
-She really does.

156
00:05:35,835 --> 00:05:37,737
-Su-ji.
-Yes?

157
00:05:37,804 --> 00:05:42,375
You're known for taking Won-hun
under your wing as a senior comedian.

158
00:05:42,442 --> 00:05:44,344
She once gave him some of her time

159
00:05:44,410 --> 00:05:48,081
to give a speech at an awards ceremony
instead of using all of her time.

160
00:05:48,147 --> 00:05:50,817
I was sitting behind him,

161
00:05:50,883 --> 00:05:53,419
and I could only see his shoulders.

162
00:05:53,486 --> 00:05:56,589
It seemed like
he was thinking he had already won.

163
00:05:56,656 --> 00:05:59,092
He looked really proud and relaxed.

164
00:05:59,158 --> 00:06:01,060
-He came ready to receive it.
-He did.

165
00:06:01,127 --> 00:06:04,597
But his shoulders got droopy
as soon as he realized he didn't win.

166
00:06:04,664 --> 00:06:06,566
-And you adore him.
-So he turned around

167
00:06:06,632 --> 00:06:10,303
and asked if I could spare him
a minute of my time

168
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:11,637
if I won an award.

169
00:06:11,704 --> 00:06:15,241
I felt really bad when he said that,

170
00:06:15,308 --> 00:06:16,542
so I gave him some of my time.

171
00:06:16,609 --> 00:06:18,010
-It was an unprecedented moment.
-I know.

172
00:06:18,077 --> 00:06:20,813
-It was a non-acceptance speech.
-"Non-acceptance speech."

173
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:23,349
I was the first person
to do that without winning an award.

174
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:24,884
You probably were.

175
00:06:24,951 --> 00:06:28,087
Should I give you some time
to give your acceptance speech?

176
00:06:28,154 --> 00:06:29,422
Yes, thank you.

177
00:06:29,489 --> 00:06:30,923
IMMEDIATELY TAKES THE OFFER

178
00:06:31,491 --> 00:06:33,192
He wrote it down!

179
00:06:33,259 --> 00:06:34,193
ALWAYS READY

180
00:06:34,260 --> 00:06:35,862
Will you pass me this as the prize?

181
00:06:37,163 --> 00:06:39,132
The Comedian of the Year.

182
00:06:39,198 --> 00:06:41,868
Kim Won-hun! Congratulations!

183
00:06:41,934 --> 00:06:43,369
ENTERTAINER OF THE YEAR
KIM WON-HUN

184
00:06:44,504 --> 00:06:46,172
HIS COLLEAGUES CELEBRATE WITH HIM

185
00:06:46,239 --> 00:06:47,974
-The flowers.
-A knife bouquet.

186
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,108
-Yes.
-A knife bouquet.

187
00:06:49,175 --> 00:06:51,110
Please share your speech.

188
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:53,413
Thank you.

189
00:06:53,479 --> 00:06:54,814
He's crying. Oh no.

190
00:06:54,881 --> 00:06:57,450
I believe no stars shine on their own.

191
00:06:57,517 --> 00:07:01,888
I want to thank everyone
who helped me shine brightly.

192
00:07:02,555 --> 00:07:03,489
LAUGH-CRY

193
00:07:04,690 --> 00:07:05,792
Everyone falls,

194
00:07:05,858 --> 00:07:07,927
but standing back up is a choice.

195
00:07:07,994 --> 00:07:09,629
-That's nice.
-I will be a comedian

196
00:07:09,695 --> 00:07:12,298
who always stands back up
even after falling.

197
00:07:12,365 --> 00:07:13,433
There's also this saying…

198
00:07:13,699 --> 00:07:14,767
BOMBARDING FAMOUS QUOTES

199
00:07:14,834 --> 00:07:18,838
-He knows too many quotes.
-…that "Those who walk through the shadows

200
00:07:18,905 --> 00:07:21,340
will see the light at the end."

201
00:07:21,407 --> 00:07:24,610
For everyone
who's walking through a dark tunnel,

202
00:07:24,677 --> 00:07:26,245
light will eventually find you,

203
00:07:26,312 --> 00:07:29,015
so please do not give up
and finish your race.

204
00:07:29,081 --> 00:07:29,916
-Anything else?
-Also,

205
00:07:29,982 --> 00:07:33,686
something great can only be done
after taking little steps.

206
00:07:33,986 --> 00:07:35,121
STAFF GIVES HIM SIGNALS

207
00:07:35,188 --> 00:07:38,658
I will continue to strive harder
and do my best. Thank you.

208
00:07:38,724 --> 00:07:41,127
Congratulations, Won-hun!

209
00:07:41,194 --> 00:07:44,130
Also, someone once said
something like this.

210
00:07:45,531 --> 00:07:48,134
I prepared an encyclopedia of quotes.

211
00:07:48,201 --> 00:07:50,870
-Yes.
-You picked out the best parts.

212
00:07:50,937 --> 00:07:54,707
-I want to do that if I ever get a chance.
-I see.

213
00:07:54,774 --> 00:07:56,676
He's also a great son.

214
00:07:56,742 --> 00:08:00,112
He got a new car for his parents
as soon as his career took off.

215
00:08:00,179 --> 00:08:03,983
I also believe he gave them
a bed made of money as a present.

216
00:08:04,050 --> 00:08:04,951
Let's take a look.

217
00:08:05,017 --> 00:08:06,452
This is it.

218
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:08,588
-It's a surprise, Mom, Dad.
<i>-It's a video.</i>

219
00:08:09,388 --> 00:08:11,624
SHOCKED PARENTS

220
00:08:11,691 --> 00:08:12,825
No way!

221
00:08:12,892 --> 00:08:15,394
-Was it ten million won?
-Yes, that's right.

222
00:08:15,461 --> 00:08:16,496
That was the money bed?

223
00:08:16,562 --> 00:08:19,365
I did that for my parents
when I first had my big break…

224
00:08:19,432 --> 00:08:21,767
-In 2022?
-…back in 2022.

225
00:08:22,101 --> 00:08:23,736
NEXT TIME, HE BOUGHT THEM A CAR

226
00:08:24,303 --> 00:08:25,538
It's the G car.

227
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:29,008
-It was for my mother.
-She must've been so thrilled.

228
00:08:29,075 --> 00:08:31,244
-She must've been.
-His parents must've been happy.

229
00:08:31,310 --> 00:08:33,246
I spent many struggling years
as an obscure comedian,

230
00:08:33,312 --> 00:08:37,350
so I always felt bad that I even had to
ask them for pocket money.

231
00:08:37,416 --> 00:08:40,853
I bought them a car
and give them cash rather often,

232
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:43,189
but they became kind of used to it.

233
00:08:43,256 --> 00:08:46,092
-Small things don't move them.
-He started from the climax.

234
00:08:46,158 --> 00:08:48,794
-All that's left is buying them a home.
-I guess that's right.

235
00:08:48,861 --> 00:08:51,797
You said one thing that changed
about your life

236
00:08:51,864 --> 00:08:54,267
is how you dine.

237
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:57,837
I now take the premium delivery option
and have it delivered directly to me.

238
00:08:57,904 --> 00:08:58,738
WOW

239
00:08:58,804 --> 00:09:00,773
-He pays that extra 1,000 won.
-The food's still hot.

240
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:04,110
-I'm always torn.
-So that was something I tried.

241
00:09:04,176 --> 00:09:06,379
-I like to flex my wealth in small ways.
-I see.

242
00:09:06,445 --> 00:09:07,446
I want to see the inside of his fridge.

243
00:09:07,513 --> 00:09:10,883
-We'll smell the scent of success.
-The rich man vibe.

244
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:13,119
-Like truffles.
-And caviar.

245
00:09:13,185 --> 00:09:15,288
I don't have truffles or caviar.

246
00:09:15,354 --> 00:09:18,224
You're watching
the 2025 <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> Championship.

247
00:09:18,291 --> 00:09:22,094
This year's championship
will be played just like baseball.

248
00:09:22,161 --> 00:09:25,097
<i>The first round is between</i>
<i>fifth-place Chef Jong-won</i>

249
00:09:25,164 --> 00:09:26,966
<i>and fourth-place Chef Eun-yeong.</i>

250
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:29,101
<i>The winner of that round will advance</i>

251
00:09:29,168 --> 00:09:31,070
<i>and go against Webtoon Artist Poong,</i>
<i>who's in third place.</i>

252
00:09:31,137 --> 00:09:34,307
The winner of the second round

253
00:09:34,373 --> 00:09:36,909
will play the third round
with Su-ji's ingredients

254
00:09:36,976 --> 00:09:39,812
<i>against second-place Chef Ho-young.</i>

255
00:09:39,879 --> 00:09:43,082
<i>The winner of that round</i>
<i>will advance to the final round</i>

256
00:09:43,149 --> 00:09:46,686
and go against the current first-place
Chef Hyun-suk.

257
00:09:46,752 --> 00:09:48,220
-That's how it'll be.
-That's crazy.

258
00:09:48,287 --> 00:09:50,790
Chefs Hyun-suk and Ho-young
must feel more relaxed.

259
00:09:50,856 --> 00:09:52,158
-Yes.
-You can just wait.

260
00:09:52,224 --> 00:09:54,460
You can cross your arms and take a rest.

261
00:09:54,527 --> 00:09:55,828
SO ANNOYING…

262
00:09:55,895 --> 00:09:57,430
You're about to fall off the chair.

263
00:09:57,496 --> 00:09:59,365
Are you taking a nap?

264
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:00,533
He's tired.

265
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:04,904
Then let's find out Won-hun's orders

266
00:10:04,971 --> 00:10:07,740
and see the themes
for the upcoming rounds.

267
00:10:07,807 --> 00:10:09,542
The tournament is already decided.

268
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:13,379
The first round, fifth versus fourth,
Jong-won versus Eun-yeong.

269
00:10:13,446 --> 00:10:15,815
What will Jong-won and Eun-yeong make?

270
00:10:15,881 --> 00:10:19,986
Please show us Won-hun's first order.

271
00:10:20,052 --> 00:10:22,088
What's his order?

272
00:10:22,154 --> 00:10:24,523
-"I Mean, I Want to Eat It Before Death."
-That sounds hard.

273
00:10:24,590 --> 00:10:26,459
I Mean, I Want to Eat It Before Death.

274
00:10:26,525 --> 00:10:29,261
-"I Mean, I Want to Eat It Before Death."
-I chose that theme

275
00:10:29,328 --> 00:10:30,796
because I eat one meal a day.

276
00:10:30,863 --> 00:10:33,866
-So whenever I order dinner…
-Really?

277
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:35,968
…I end up spending a lot of time
imagining things,

278
00:10:36,035 --> 00:10:40,873
such as "What would I eat
as the last meal of my life?"

279
00:10:40,940 --> 00:10:44,043
-I want to eat the best meal today.
-The best meal.

280
00:10:44,110 --> 00:10:45,645
It's a perfect theme.

281
00:10:45,711 --> 00:10:50,883
This is the theme for the round
between Chef Jong-won and Chef Eun-yeong.

282
00:10:50,950 --> 00:10:52,885
Let's find out the next order.

283
00:10:52,952 --> 00:10:54,720
It's for the first round winner and Poong.

284
00:10:54,787 --> 00:10:56,956
"I Mean, I Want to Eat It With Beer."

285
00:10:57,023 --> 00:10:58,190
I Mean, I Want to Eat It With Beer.

286
00:10:58,257 --> 00:10:59,825
I Mean, I Want to Eat It With Beer.

287
00:11:00,026 --> 00:11:00,926
GOOD JOB

288
00:11:00,993 --> 00:11:05,097
I often eat my dinner with beer.

289
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:09,502
-So I wanted something that would go well…
-Beer snack.

290
00:11:09,568 --> 00:11:10,603
…with some beer.

291
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:12,438
-Got it.
-Wait, that's his thing.

292
00:11:12,505 --> 00:11:14,373
Poong, Eun-yeong, and Jong-won,

293
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:16,676
the three who'll cook
with Won-hun's ingredients,

294
00:11:16,742 --> 00:11:20,413
keep the theme in your mind
as you look through his fridge.

295
00:11:20,479 --> 00:11:24,216
We're now about to rummage
through his fridge.

296
00:11:24,283 --> 00:11:25,918
Have you moved out now?

297
00:11:25,985 --> 00:11:27,787
Yes, and I'm married.

298
00:11:27,853 --> 00:11:29,121
I didn't know you were married.

299
00:11:29,188 --> 00:11:32,058
-It's been three, no, four years.
-He keeps hiding it.

300
00:11:32,725 --> 00:11:33,759
So it was a secret?

301
00:11:33,826 --> 00:11:35,761
It's been four years?

302
00:11:35,828 --> 00:11:38,064
-It's my fourth year.
-Your fourth year.

303
00:11:38,130 --> 00:11:39,532
-The fourth year.
-I wonder what he has.

304
00:11:39,598 --> 00:11:42,601
-He's a big success now…
-Yes.

305
00:11:42,668 --> 00:11:44,804
-…so he must have piles of delicacies.
-Exactly.

306
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:46,138
I'm dying to find out.

307
00:11:46,205 --> 00:11:47,606
The hottest of the hottest,

308
00:11:47,673 --> 00:11:49,842
-we present Won-hun's fridge!
-Won-hun's fridge!

309
00:11:49,909 --> 00:11:51,444
I MEAN, WE LOOK FORWARD TO
SEEING HIS FRIDGE

310
00:11:52,144 --> 00:11:54,113
HE HAS LOTS OF INGREDIENTS

311
00:11:54,180 --> 00:11:55,114
-Won-hun's fridge!
-Won-hun's fridge!

312
00:11:55,181 --> 00:11:56,749
PRESENTING WON-HUN'S FRIDGE

313
00:11:56,816 --> 00:11:58,884
-That's a lot.
-He has lots of food.

314
00:12:00,252 --> 00:12:03,656
I probably have many ingredients
you can use for your dish.

315
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:06,459
First off, the second shelf.

316
00:12:06,525 --> 00:12:09,562
I see some side dishes and kimchi.

317
00:12:09,628 --> 00:12:11,163
Man.

318
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:12,898
-What is it?
-What does he have?

319
00:12:12,965 --> 00:12:16,435
-I believe we mostly have meal kits.
-What is it?

320
00:12:16,502 --> 00:12:18,104
He gets his food at a department store.

321
00:12:18,971 --> 00:12:21,907
-The side dishes? Yes.
-The side dishes there are so pricey.

322
00:12:21,974 --> 00:12:24,777
Wait, no. They aren't too expensive.

323
00:12:24,844 --> 00:12:26,712
This small thing costs 6,500 won.

324
00:12:26,779 --> 00:12:28,447
SEASONED CUCUMBER AND CHIVES

325
00:12:28,514 --> 00:12:30,282
Braised fish cake, 6,500 won.

326
00:12:30,349 --> 00:12:31,751
Braised fish cake costs 6,500 won?

327
00:12:31,817 --> 00:12:33,919
All these amount to about 30,000 won.

328
00:12:34,186 --> 00:12:35,955
AUTOMATIC RESPONSE

329
00:12:36,021 --> 00:12:37,056
It's not that expensive!

330
00:12:37,123 --> 00:12:39,792
-He gets his food at a department store.
-That's amazing.

331
00:12:39,859 --> 00:12:40,860
That's the full price,

332
00:12:40,926 --> 00:12:43,596
but I got four packs for 12,000
because I got them just before it closed.

333
00:12:43,662 --> 00:12:44,630
They were affordable.

334
00:12:44,697 --> 00:12:48,100
We both work,
so we mostly buy our side dishes.

335
00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:51,370
-Anyway, he gets it at a department store.
-At times, it's cheaper there.

336
00:12:51,437 --> 00:12:54,840
-He's a big success.
-One of the two orders was about beer.

337
00:12:54,907 --> 00:12:57,510
-Keep an eye on it, Poong.
-Yes, the beer.

338
00:12:57,576 --> 00:12:58,944
How much alcohol can you take?

339
00:12:59,512 --> 00:13:02,047
-Well, the thing is…
-Yes?

340
00:13:02,114 --> 00:13:03,549
…I've never been drunk.

341
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:05,117
-What?
-I've never seen him drunk.

342
00:13:05,184 --> 00:13:06,352
-I'm not trying to show off.
-No?

343
00:13:06,418 --> 00:13:08,587
I guess I have a really strong liver.

344
00:13:08,654 --> 00:13:10,022
How many bottles of soju?

345
00:13:10,089 --> 00:13:12,925
-On a good day, about five bottles.
-Five bottles?

346
00:13:12,992 --> 00:13:15,127
-That's a lot.
-You're good with alcohol.

347
00:13:15,194 --> 00:13:16,462
You can handle it.

348
00:13:16,529 --> 00:13:19,431
I see things like perilla seed powder,

349
00:13:19,498 --> 00:13:21,000
as well as bracken.

350
00:13:21,066 --> 00:13:23,002
I found the veggies.

351
00:13:23,068 --> 00:13:27,406
Eggplants, napa cabbage,
lettuce, and a carrot.

352
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:28,908
I love raw vegetables,

353
00:13:28,974 --> 00:13:31,110
so I love to make veggie wraps.

354
00:13:31,177 --> 00:13:32,745
-Look at these.
-These are for wraps.

355
00:13:32,812 --> 00:13:34,647
I really love that napa cabbage.

356
00:13:34,713 --> 00:13:36,348
He has napa cabbage here.

357
00:13:36,415 --> 00:13:38,184
I see some fruits.
Strawberries, grapes, tangerines.

358
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:39,552
Shine muscat.

359
00:13:39,618 --> 00:13:41,120
And lots of lemons.

360
00:13:41,187 --> 00:13:42,688
Do you enjoy lemons?

361
00:13:42,755 --> 00:13:45,191
I love anything sour,

362
00:13:45,257 --> 00:13:46,826
-so I eat those instead of tangerines.
-Sourness.

363
00:13:46,892 --> 00:13:48,194
-What?
-Instead of tangerines?

364
00:13:48,260 --> 00:13:50,129
-You eat this as is?
-Stop lying.

365
00:13:50,196 --> 00:13:52,131
Sourness doesn't taste strong to me,

366
00:13:52,198 --> 00:13:53,332
so I really love it.

367
00:13:53,399 --> 00:13:55,801
-Really? He's lying.
-We have to check.

368
00:13:55,868 --> 00:13:57,903
-It's not a tangerine.
-We're going to check.

369
00:13:57,970 --> 00:14:00,072
-It doesn't taste sour to me.
-It has to be.

370
00:14:00,139 --> 00:14:02,308
He eats lemons as if they were tangerines.

371
00:14:02,374 --> 00:14:04,076
Even farmers wouldn't eat it like that.

372
00:14:04,143 --> 00:14:05,444
-It looks sour.
-It's not.

373
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:08,247
Comedians love to put on funny skits,

374
00:14:08,314 --> 00:14:10,149
so he might do something like this.

375
00:14:10,716 --> 00:14:11,617
NICE ONE

376
00:14:11,684 --> 00:14:12,918
Are you trying to build this up?

377
00:14:12,985 --> 00:14:15,087
-I don't like those skits.
-That's old.

378
00:14:15,154 --> 00:14:16,355
Are you building it up?

379
00:14:16,422 --> 00:14:19,358
-Don't drool.
-I can't watch this.

380
00:14:20,092 --> 00:14:24,129
TAKES A HUGE BITE

381
00:14:24,730 --> 00:14:26,899
EATING IT WITH THEIR EYES

382
00:14:26,966 --> 00:14:28,901
PEACEFUL

383
00:14:28,968 --> 00:14:30,002
My mouth feels itchy.

384
00:14:30,769 --> 00:14:32,438
It's really good.

385
00:14:32,504 --> 00:14:34,006
-His face didn't change.
-It was real.

386
00:14:34,073 --> 00:14:35,708
How many of those do you eat at once?

387
00:14:35,774 --> 00:14:38,711
-One or two.
-Really?

388
00:14:38,777 --> 00:14:40,813
-But your eyes get a bit wet.
-They're teary.

389
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:41,981
The thing is,

390
00:14:42,548 --> 00:14:44,250
I was thinking of something.

391
00:14:44,817 --> 00:14:45,985
SUDDENLY REMEMBERED SOMETHING SAD

392
00:14:46,051 --> 00:14:47,653
It was a touching video I saw.

393
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:48,654
Throw that into your mouth.

394
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:50,089
-The whole thing?
-Yes.

395
00:14:50,155 --> 00:14:52,258
-You're lying!
-You said you eat one or two.

396
00:14:52,324 --> 00:14:55,261
-Maybe it's not too sour.
-Well, I can eat it,

397
00:14:55,327 --> 00:14:57,162
but we're supposed to take
a certain amount of vitamins a day.

398
00:14:58,664 --> 00:15:01,367
Give me that for a second. Is it not sour?

399
00:15:01,433 --> 00:15:03,969
Some lemons are not that sour.

400
00:15:04,036 --> 00:15:05,971
Aren't all lemons sour?

401
00:15:06,038 --> 00:15:07,907
Try it. Just eat the whole thing.

402
00:15:07,973 --> 00:15:08,908
ELECTRIFYING

403
00:15:10,576 --> 00:15:11,911
PASSING IT ON SMOOTHLY

404
00:15:12,177 --> 00:15:13,913
WHY IS HE JUST LETTING IT HAPPEN?

405
00:15:14,213 --> 00:15:15,681
A BIG FROWN

406
00:15:17,049 --> 00:15:19,418
-You're something else.
-I actually eat it like this.

407
00:15:19,485 --> 00:15:21,453
-That's way too sour.
-Are you all right?

408
00:15:22,087 --> 00:15:23,722
I guess I got used to it.

409
00:15:23,789 --> 00:15:24,657
COUGH

410
00:15:24,723 --> 00:15:26,025
No, that was…

411
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:28,127
-Are you about to throw up?
-Clearing your throat?

412
00:15:28,193 --> 00:15:30,095
It's not because it's sour. I choked.

413
00:15:30,162 --> 00:15:31,563
COULDN'T MISS A CHANCE TO BE FUNNY

414
00:15:31,630 --> 00:15:33,966
He doesn't find most food sour,
so remember that.

415
00:15:34,033 --> 00:15:35,301
-You should use a lot.
-Pour it in.

416
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:38,003
Next, the freezer.

417
00:15:38,070 --> 00:15:39,605
What does he have?

418
00:15:39,672 --> 00:15:42,374
I see some meat here, beef,

419
00:15:42,441 --> 00:15:44,410
bacon, pork.

420
00:15:44,476 --> 00:15:46,879
The next drawer has seafood.

421
00:15:47,479 --> 00:15:50,482
Shrimp, mackerel, and marinated salmon.

422
00:15:50,549 --> 00:15:51,750
-Marinated salmon?
-Yes.

423
00:15:51,817 --> 00:15:52,918
-That sounds good.
-Marinated salmon.

424
00:15:52,985 --> 00:15:54,420
I love seafood too.

425
00:15:54,486 --> 00:15:55,487
What's your favorite?

426
00:15:55,554 --> 00:15:58,657
Anything made with shrimp, honestly.

427
00:15:58,724 --> 00:16:00,592
-So you like shrimp.
-I do.

428
00:16:00,659 --> 00:16:03,362
These are all meal kits. And this drawer.

429
00:16:03,429 --> 00:16:05,564
I think I found some cheese.

430
00:16:05,631 --> 00:16:08,300
And bread. He has lots of cheese.

431
00:16:08,367 --> 00:16:10,536
We often cook Western cuisine at home,

432
00:16:10,602 --> 00:16:14,440
-and almost everything has cheese in it.
-I see.

433
00:16:14,506 --> 00:16:16,108
We just looked through Won-hun's fridge,

434
00:16:16,175 --> 00:16:20,446
which has more than enough
to make your dishes.

435
00:16:20,512 --> 00:16:23,315
2025 <i>Chef & My Fridge </i>Championship.

436
00:16:23,382 --> 00:16:26,118
The first round begins now!

437
00:16:26,185 --> 00:16:29,221
THE LONG-AWAITED ROUND 1 BEGINS NOW

438
00:16:29,288 --> 00:16:32,324
<i>2025 </i>Chef & My Fridge<i> Championship,</i>

439
00:16:32,391 --> 00:16:35,761
<i>held with ingredients</i>
<i>from Won-hun's fridge.</i>

440
00:16:35,828 --> 00:16:38,597
<i>This is the opening game.</i>

441
00:16:38,664 --> 00:16:40,332
Fifth place in the regular season,

442
00:16:40,399 --> 00:16:43,902
the official good vibes guy of the show,
Chef Son Jong-won.

443
00:16:43,969 --> 00:16:45,971
Fourth place in the regular season,

444
00:16:46,038 --> 00:16:51,043
the official moth to a flame of the show,
Chef Park Eun-yeong.

445
00:16:51,110 --> 00:16:53,512
It may be disappointing for Jong-won,

446
00:16:53,579 --> 00:16:56,115
<i>because if he had won previously,</i>

447
00:16:56,181 --> 00:16:59,251
he could've been in second place
with ten wins.

448
00:16:59,318 --> 00:17:01,120
-But you lost against Ho-young.
-What a shame.

449
00:17:01,186 --> 00:17:02,488
AHEM

450
00:17:02,554 --> 00:17:05,024
So he moved up to second place.

451
00:17:05,090 --> 00:17:06,492
See you later.

452
00:17:06,558 --> 00:17:09,061
-See you later.
-That put Jong-won in fifth place.

453
00:17:09,128 --> 00:17:11,997
IT'S RARE TO SEE
A CONCEITED HO-YOUNG

454
00:17:12,064 --> 00:17:14,333
Look how he's crossing his short arms.

455
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:16,035
You don't look comfortable.

456
00:17:16,101 --> 00:17:17,669
He's crossing his legs too.

457
00:17:17,736 --> 00:17:19,571
I doubt that's physically possible.

458
00:17:19,638 --> 00:17:21,340
A single star made a huge difference.

459
00:17:21,407 --> 00:17:23,375
One took second place,
the other took fifth.

460
00:17:23,442 --> 00:17:25,144
Up against him is Chef Eun-yeong,

461
00:17:25,210 --> 00:17:27,846
the only one among the young'uns

462
00:17:27,913 --> 00:17:30,182
to make it to the championship.

463
00:17:30,249 --> 00:17:32,217
I'm a little anxious

464
00:17:32,284 --> 00:17:33,952
because I want at least one win,

465
00:17:34,019 --> 00:17:37,089
but I have to play the first round
against Chef Jong-won.

466
00:17:37,156 --> 00:17:39,024
-He's too good.
-No, don't talk like a weakling.

467
00:17:39,091 --> 00:17:40,492
So I'm a bit nervous.

468
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:43,429
You two have fought twice,
won one and lost one each.

469
00:17:43,495 --> 00:17:45,330
-It's neck-and-neck.
-It is.

470
00:17:45,397 --> 00:17:47,599
Also, even if you win this round,

471
00:17:47,666 --> 00:17:49,234
you must make it past Poong

472
00:17:49,301 --> 00:17:51,070
to reach Ho-young.

473
00:17:51,737 --> 00:17:53,138
You have to win four times
to be the champion.

474
00:17:53,372 --> 00:17:54,540
MUST WIN 4 TIMES TO BE THE CHAMPION

475
00:17:54,606 --> 00:17:56,208
-That sounds tough.
-Actually,

476
00:17:56,275 --> 00:17:59,011
I thought it'd be fun
to rise up from the bottom.

477
00:17:59,078 --> 00:18:01,513
-I came with all seriousness.
-He's so cool.

478
00:18:01,580 --> 00:18:03,348
Chef Hyun-suk, wait for me.

479
00:18:04,183 --> 00:18:05,484
He's so cool!

480
00:18:05,551 --> 00:18:06,885
SEE YOU AT THE FINALS

481
00:18:06,952 --> 00:18:09,421
-I'll prove the power of the young'uns.
-Of course.

482
00:18:09,488 --> 00:18:11,156
CAN YOU STOP ME?

483
00:18:11,223 --> 00:18:12,491
I'll root for Eun-yeong.

484
00:18:14,359 --> 00:18:16,295
CHEF JONG-WON'S INGREDIENTS:
BEEF TENDERLOIN, GALBI SAUCE, BRACKEN,

485
00:18:16,361 --> 00:18:18,530
BRAISED FISH CAKE, SEASONED GARLIC STEM,
MUKEUNJI, LETTUCE, CARROT, AND MORE

486
00:18:18,597 --> 00:18:20,966
What are you making, Chef Jong-won?

487
00:18:21,033 --> 00:18:23,735
The name of my dish is

488
00:18:23,802 --> 00:18:26,872
"Your Son's Too Hot,
Sorry Mom's Lunch Box."

489
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:28,507
-Right.
-The lyrics.

490
00:18:28,574 --> 00:18:29,641
-The BTS song.
-Yes.

491
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:32,444
-j-hope performed that line in France.
-Yes.

492
00:18:32,511 --> 00:18:34,480
As someone who makes food,

493
00:18:34,546 --> 00:18:37,416
I thought I would want to eat
something warm and familiar

494
00:18:37,483 --> 00:18:41,553
if I were to eat one last meal
before my death.

495
00:18:41,620 --> 00:18:43,856
Like a home-cooked meal made by a mom.

496
00:18:43,922 --> 00:18:45,090
Playing that sentimental factor.

497
00:18:45,157 --> 00:18:46,358
That's a guaranteed win.

498
00:18:46,425 --> 00:18:48,227
And I heard he was such a good son.

499
00:18:48,293 --> 00:18:50,028
-I already feel sad.
-You brought it up twice.

500
00:18:50,095 --> 00:18:51,663
I'm already moved.

501
00:18:51,730 --> 00:18:53,699
-He read his mind.
-I got touched before I tried it.

502
00:18:53,765 --> 00:18:55,667
So I plan to make <i>gimbap.</i>

503
00:18:55,734 --> 00:18:57,803
It may seem simple,

504
00:18:57,870 --> 00:18:59,838
but compared to how ordinary it seems,

505
00:18:59,905 --> 00:19:02,341
it requires a lot of work to make it.

506
00:19:02,407 --> 00:19:04,776
I'll use your side dishes to make <i>gimbap.</i>

507
00:19:04,843 --> 00:19:06,011
It's just what I like.

508
00:19:06,078 --> 00:19:08,280
Also, rolled omelet
is a staple in a mom's meals.

509
00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:10,516
So I want to make that

510
00:19:10,582 --> 00:19:12,384
and serve it with <i>doenjang </i>soup.

511
00:19:12,451 --> 00:19:14,753
-I love it.
-A meal for the good son.

512
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:16,755
I love <i>gimbap</i> too,

513
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:20,492
so I'm already excited
to steal one from him.

514
00:19:20,859 --> 00:19:22,761
THAT'S A TOUGH ONE…

515
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:25,030
Chef Jong-won is also a great son.

516
00:19:25,864 --> 00:19:26,932
The good son couple.

517
00:19:27,132 --> 00:19:28,534
SORRY?

518
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:30,669
She called the two good sons
the good son couple.

519
00:19:30,736 --> 00:19:33,672
I no longer feel like
being a good son is the point.

520
00:19:33,739 --> 00:19:36,875
-I mean, it's the two of you.
-Was that what you meant?

521
00:19:36,942 --> 00:19:39,678
We wonder if the good son couple
will work with each other.

522
00:19:40,612 --> 00:19:41,880
CHEF EUN-YEONG'S INGREDIENTS:

523
00:19:41,947 --> 00:19:44,683
BOILED BRACKEN, PORK BELLY,
MUKEUNJI, PERILLA OIL, OYSTER SAUCE

524
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:47,953
Up against him is Chef Eun-yeong.
What's your dish called?

525
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:50,989
My dish is called

526
00:19:51,623 --> 00:19:53,025
I Mean, Rice Is Great Before Passing.

527
00:19:53,091 --> 00:19:55,360
I Mean, Rice Is Great Before Passing.

528
00:19:55,427 --> 00:19:59,064
-She got it. She's good.
-"I Mean, Rice Is Great Before Passing."

529
00:19:59,131 --> 00:20:00,265
Did she do a good job?

530
00:20:00,332 --> 00:20:02,601
Yes, I loved it.
She was much better than you.

531
00:20:02,668 --> 00:20:04,870
Yes, she's good. She's much better.

532
00:20:04,937 --> 00:20:06,238
Are you making rice?

533
00:20:06,305 --> 00:20:09,875
I thought you should warm your body up
before you pass away to the other--

534
00:20:09,942 --> 00:20:11,643
-Pass away to where?
-He's not leaving.

535
00:20:11,710 --> 00:20:13,645
I'm not actually passing away.
It's just a scenario.

536
00:20:13,712 --> 00:20:15,314
She might light up incense sticks.

537
00:20:15,380 --> 00:20:16,848
It's not for a memorial.

538
00:20:16,915 --> 00:20:19,418
-We aren't making food for his memorial.
-Should we pay our respect?

539
00:20:19,484 --> 00:20:20,919
Well, he has to pass.

540
00:20:20,986 --> 00:20:22,654
-Go where?
-Look at him.

541
00:20:22,721 --> 00:20:24,623
Everyone has to pass away at some point.

542
00:20:24,690 --> 00:20:27,426
I thought it'd be nice
if you had a warm meal before you left.

543
00:20:27,492 --> 00:20:28,460
Are you making fresh rice?

544
00:20:28,527 --> 00:20:30,963
Yes, I'll make rice in a stone pot

545
00:20:31,029 --> 00:20:32,097
-and make sure he leaves…
-Rice in a stone pot.

546
00:20:32,164 --> 00:20:33,599
…with a full belly.

547
00:20:33,665 --> 00:20:35,634
-Is this okay?
-Go where?

548
00:20:35,701 --> 00:20:37,869
-Are you working for a funeral agency?
-It's the theme.

549
00:20:37,936 --> 00:20:39,271
Even her apron is black.

550
00:20:39,338 --> 00:20:40,606
-You're right.
-It's black.

551
00:20:40,672 --> 00:20:44,409
-You wanted the pre-death food.
-She wants you to have a full belly.

552
00:20:44,476 --> 00:20:46,445
She truly is a Successful Maniac.

553
00:20:46,511 --> 00:20:47,346
LIVING UP TO HER NICKNAME

554
00:20:47,412 --> 00:20:49,147
Hong Kong has a stone pot rice

555
00:20:49,214 --> 00:20:51,416
called <i>bo zai fan</i>, or claypot rice,

556
00:20:51,483 --> 00:20:55,320
and you can add toppings of your choice
on top of the rice.

557
00:20:55,387 --> 00:20:57,990
So I want to make you
a pot of <i>bo zai fan</i>, but a Korean version.

558
00:20:58,056 --> 00:20:59,691
-I'm looking forward to this.
-Right.

559
00:20:59,758 --> 00:21:01,560
-We have an announcement before we begin.
-Yes.

560
00:21:01,627 --> 00:21:04,896
Sung-ju went out for the interim check
during the last regular round.

561
00:21:04,963 --> 00:21:06,531
Can he continue his family's legacy?

562
00:21:06,598 --> 00:21:08,400
It's a bit bland for my taste.

563
00:21:08,467 --> 00:21:10,235
But it's a bit too strong in its flavor.

564
00:21:10,302 --> 00:21:12,537
-What happened, Sung-ju?
-Yes, you said it was bland!

565
00:21:12,604 --> 00:21:16,074
It was bland
when he had four minutes left.

566
00:21:16,141 --> 00:21:18,277
People said he must've lost
his sense of taste.

567
00:21:19,211 --> 00:21:21,747
-There was such a suspicion.
-That's true.

568
00:21:21,813 --> 00:21:23,849
Because today's rounds are very important,

569
00:21:23,915 --> 00:21:25,984
the three chefs who are sitting out today

570
00:21:26,051 --> 00:21:29,087
will go out as assistants today
for the interim check.

571
00:21:30,389 --> 00:21:31,857
Sung-jun, you'll do this round.

572
00:21:31,923 --> 00:21:34,326
-I'll get ready.
-I'll go with Sung-jun.

573
00:21:34,393 --> 00:21:38,063
Let us begin the round
between fourth and fifth place.

574
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:39,598
-Why am I nervous?
-For the loser,

575
00:21:39,665 --> 00:21:44,002
this will be the final round of this year.

576
00:21:44,636 --> 00:21:49,074
Let us begin round one
of the championship.

577
00:21:49,141 --> 00:21:50,976
Man, look at the vibe.

578
00:21:51,043 --> 00:21:52,844
The air is different today.

579
00:21:53,145 --> 00:21:55,847
CHAMPIONSHIP ROUND 1

580
00:21:55,914 --> 00:21:57,082
Jeez.

581
00:21:57,149 --> 00:21:58,717
-It's definitely different today.
-It is.

582
00:21:58,784 --> 00:22:02,321
She wishes to charge forward
and seize her personal trophy,

583
00:22:02,387 --> 00:22:05,324
the moth to a flame of the show,
Chef Park Eun-yeong.

584
00:22:05,390 --> 00:22:06,325
You got this, Eun-yeong.

585
00:22:06,391 --> 00:22:09,027
He will start at the bottom
and become the champion.

586
00:22:09,094 --> 00:22:13,565
The man who wants to write a new history,
Chef Son Jong-won.

587
00:22:13,632 --> 00:22:16,568
Which one of them
will become Poong's opponent?

588
00:22:16,635 --> 00:22:19,705
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

589
00:22:19,771 --> 00:22:20,672
-Let's go!
-Go!

590
00:22:22,641 --> 00:22:25,110
THE FIRST ROUND BEGINS!

591
00:22:25,177 --> 00:22:27,379
Let's go. Start with the rice.

592
00:22:27,679 --> 00:22:29,214
THE MOST IMPORTANT PART
OF STONE POT RICE, RICE

593
00:22:29,281 --> 00:22:30,749
You have to hurry, Eun-yeong.

594
00:22:30,816 --> 00:22:31,683
Yes, the stone pot rice.

595
00:22:32,451 --> 00:22:34,453
-You have to hurry.
-She measures the amount of water.

596
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:35,754
Just enough to cover the rice.

597
00:22:35,821 --> 00:22:38,256
Chef Eun-yeong
works on the stone pot rice!

598
00:22:38,323 --> 00:22:41,493
-She said she'd top that with something.
-Yes, she said toppings.

599
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:43,829
Because she'll top it
with other ingredients,

600
00:22:43,895 --> 00:22:46,631
she must also think of the water
they'll give off or take.

601
00:22:46,698 --> 00:22:49,534
Is Hong Kong-style stone pot rice mushy?

602
00:22:49,601 --> 00:22:50,669
It'll be light and fluffy.

603
00:22:50,736 --> 00:22:52,604
-Light and fluffy.
-Light and fluffy.

604
00:22:52,671 --> 00:22:54,172
She might make excuses later and say,

605
00:22:54,239 --> 00:22:55,941
"Hong Kong-style rice is mushy."

606
00:22:56,007 --> 00:22:57,442
SHE'S DONE THAT BEFORE

607
00:22:58,377 --> 00:22:59,678
I'll take some water out.

608
00:23:00,679 --> 00:23:02,814
Eun-yeong scoops some water out.

609
00:23:02,881 --> 00:23:03,915
You can't make porridge

610
00:23:03,982 --> 00:23:07,853
and say something like, "I made porridge,
so it's easier to eat before you die."

611
00:23:07,919 --> 00:23:09,788
"You're dying,
so I made porridge, which is dead rice."

612
00:23:09,855 --> 00:23:11,123
No such excuses.

613
00:23:11,189 --> 00:23:12,224
Fine.

614
00:23:12,290 --> 00:23:13,392
Light and fluffy…

615
00:23:13,458 --> 00:23:14,393
SHE FINDS IT FUNNY TOO

616
00:23:14,459 --> 00:23:16,228
She's using bracken.

617
00:23:16,294 --> 00:23:18,597
-Yes, it's bracken.
-That must be a topping.

618
00:23:18,663 --> 00:23:20,298
Chef Jong-won uses instant rice.

619
00:23:20,365 --> 00:23:23,902
-It's impossible to make fresh rice.
-There's not enough time.

620
00:23:23,969 --> 00:23:27,105
I think he's grinding meat in a blender.

621
00:23:27,172 --> 00:23:28,607
What's that meat?

622
00:23:28,673 --> 00:23:30,308
-Beef tenderloin.
-Tenderloin.

623
00:23:30,375 --> 00:23:31,810
He's using beef tenderloin.

624
00:23:31,877 --> 00:23:32,978
GROUND TENDERLOIN

625
00:23:33,044 --> 00:23:34,880
GALBI SAUCE, CRUSHED GARLIC

626
00:23:34,946 --> 00:23:36,648
-Making <i>gimbap</i> in 15 minutes…
-They're so busy.

627
00:23:36,715 --> 00:23:38,483
…is much harder than you think.

628
00:23:38,550 --> 00:23:41,386
-It requires lots of ingredients.
-Yes, and it takes a lot of work.

629
00:23:42,421 --> 00:23:44,189
Are you stir-frying ground beef?

630
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:45,924
-Yes.
-It's ground, marinated with <i>galbi </i>sauce,

631
00:23:45,991 --> 00:23:46,958
and cooked in sesame oil.

632
00:23:47,225 --> 00:23:48,059
MAIN GIMBAP FILLING: BEEF

633
00:23:48,126 --> 00:23:49,628
It must be for the <i>gimbap.</i>

634
00:23:49,961 --> 00:23:51,029
GLANCES

635
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:53,932
ACCELERATING INGREDIENT PREPARATION

636
00:23:54,499 --> 00:23:55,333
Pork belly.

637
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:57,936
Chef Eun-yeong is using pork belly.

638
00:23:58,003 --> 00:24:00,472
-Yes.
-How will you use it for the pot rice?

639
00:24:00,539 --> 00:24:04,409
I'll stir-fry it in Chinese-style
and top it on the rice later.

640
00:24:04,643 --> 00:24:05,744
WOW

641
00:24:05,811 --> 00:24:07,179
-A stir-fried topping.
-Please use lots.

642
00:24:07,245 --> 00:24:09,614
What kind of personal creation
are you adding today?

643
00:24:09,681 --> 00:24:10,715
CHUCKLES

644
00:24:10,782 --> 00:24:13,185
I'm using bracken,
so that makes it my personal creation.

645
00:24:14,853 --> 00:24:17,389
It's modified
from the actual Hong Kong-style dish.

646
00:24:17,456 --> 00:24:19,958
She's using bracken,
so it's her own creation.

647
00:24:20,025 --> 00:24:23,495
2. STIR-FRY CRUSHED GARLIC, BRACKEN,
SOY SAUCE, AND PERILLA OIL

648
00:24:23,562 --> 00:24:26,565
Chef Eun-yeong is putting lots of work
into the bracken.

649
00:24:27,265 --> 00:24:28,467
YOUR PERSONAL BRACKEN?

650
00:24:28,533 --> 00:24:29,367
SESAME OIL

651
00:24:29,434 --> 00:24:30,635
Sesame oil and bracken.

652
00:24:30,702 --> 00:24:32,504
They're both using bracken.

653
00:24:32,571 --> 00:24:33,772
It'd taste good in <i>gimbap.</i>

654
00:24:33,839 --> 00:24:36,875
He has to finish
cooking the fillings first…

655
00:24:36,942 --> 00:24:38,510
-Yes.
-…before he can roll the <i>gimbap.</i>

656
00:24:38,577 --> 00:24:40,645
-That's why it takes a long time.
-That's right.

657
00:24:40,712 --> 00:24:44,115
-How does he manage all those pans?
-I know, right?

658
00:24:44,749 --> 00:24:46,718
It's been three minutes.

659
00:24:46,918 --> 00:24:48,119
SIZZLING…

660
00:24:49,221 --> 00:24:50,789
Eun-yeong, something smells burnt.

661
00:24:51,690 --> 00:24:52,691
Is it okay, Eun-yeong?

662
00:24:53,692 --> 00:24:55,494
-It could've been bad.
-It could've been, right?

663
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:56,928
-I saved you.
-Yes, thanks.

664
00:24:57,496 --> 00:24:58,330
Hurry up.

665
00:24:59,197 --> 00:25:01,132
It takes a lot of work to make <i>gimbap.</i>

666
00:25:01,666 --> 00:25:02,901
-Four eggs?
-For rolled omelet?

667
00:25:03,134 --> 00:25:05,003
2. SEASON BEATEN EGGS WITH SALT AND PEPPER

668
00:25:05,070 --> 00:25:06,404
Rolled omelet is important.

669
00:25:06,471 --> 00:25:08,073
You said you'd make <i>jjigae</i> too.

670
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:10,175
You also have to make <i>jjigae.</i>

671
00:25:10,942 --> 00:25:12,644
You said you'd make <i>doenjang jjigae.</i>

672
00:25:12,711 --> 00:25:13,979
MAKING HIM ANXIOUS WITH HIS WORDS

673
00:25:14,045 --> 00:25:15,247
You're running out of time.

674
00:25:15,313 --> 00:25:17,249
I'm going to do it. Jeez, don't worry.

675
00:25:17,315 --> 00:25:18,850
You might run out of time.

676
00:25:18,917 --> 00:25:21,553
It smells so good right now.

677
00:25:21,620 --> 00:25:24,656
Some people like <i>gimbap </i>with lots of rice,

678
00:25:24,723 --> 00:25:25,891
while others prefer more fillings.

679
00:25:25,957 --> 00:25:28,260
I don't want too much rice.

680
00:25:28,326 --> 00:25:29,828
-Hey, less rice!
-Chef Jong-won!

681
00:25:29,895 --> 00:25:32,097
-He prefers less rice.
-He likes it with less rice.

682
00:25:32,163 --> 00:25:34,799
-He likes it with lots of rice.
-He doesn't like thick <i>gimbap</i>.

683
00:25:34,866 --> 00:25:36,201
He prefers less rice!

684
00:25:36,268 --> 00:25:38,470
Chef Sung-jun is sabotaging me,
so I can't hear anything.

685
00:25:38,537 --> 00:25:40,705
He likes <i>gimbap</i> with less rice!

686
00:25:40,772 --> 00:25:41,806
Got it.

687
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:44,910
-No, he said lots of rice.
-Sung-jun is sabotaging him.

688
00:25:44,976 --> 00:25:48,046
-He just gave him the wrong information.
-Go, Eun-yeong!

689
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:49,414
SALT

690
00:25:49,748 --> 00:25:51,917
3. ADD EGG INTO BOILING SALT WATER
AND POACH

691
00:25:51,983 --> 00:25:53,418
She's poaching an egg.

692
00:25:53,485 --> 00:25:55,220
-She's poaching an egg.
-That's a great choice.

693
00:25:55,287 --> 00:25:56,187
Poached eggs are delicious.

694
00:25:56,454 --> 00:25:57,989
JONG-WON CHOPS CARROTS

695
00:25:58,690 --> 00:26:01,459
Why is he chopping carrots
into pieces like that? It's for <i>gimbap.</i>

696
00:26:01,526 --> 00:26:03,028
-That's too thick.
-You're right.

697
00:26:03,094 --> 00:26:04,629
Shouldn't you julienne them?

698
00:26:04,696 --> 00:26:07,265
You're right.
Wouldn't that be too hard to eat?

699
00:26:07,332 --> 00:26:08,667
He's on the fence.

700
00:26:09,034 --> 00:26:10,869
INSTEAD OF ANSWERING…

701
00:26:12,137 --> 00:26:13,605
DICING INTO SMALLER PIECES!

702
00:26:13,672 --> 00:26:15,340
Aren't those for the rolled omelet?

703
00:26:15,407 --> 00:26:16,708
It's for the rolled omelet.

704
00:26:16,775 --> 00:26:19,277
-For the rolled omelet.
-Rolled omelet?

705
00:26:19,344 --> 00:26:21,713
Chef Jong-won always has a plan
for every dish.

706
00:26:21,780 --> 00:26:23,715
NEXT, GREEN ONION

707
00:26:24,115 --> 00:26:25,083
INTO SIMILAR TINY PIECES!

708
00:26:25,150 --> 00:26:26,318
Look at him perform.

709
00:26:27,953 --> 00:26:29,387
-He's making it look pretty.
-He's fast.

710
00:26:29,454 --> 00:26:31,489
ADDING DELICATE TOUCHES
TO THE ROLLED OMELET

711
00:26:32,090 --> 00:26:33,391
Actually, I prepared

712
00:26:33,458 --> 00:26:35,560
a thermal lunch box today.

713
00:26:35,627 --> 00:26:37,162
-Thermal?
-When I was younger,

714
00:26:37,228 --> 00:26:39,297
I used to pack my lunches in one of those.

715
00:26:39,364 --> 00:26:41,199
Like for school trips.

716
00:26:41,266 --> 00:26:42,734
-Yes.
-School trips.

717
00:26:42,801 --> 00:26:44,336
-I'm about to cry.
-Moms would make…

718
00:26:44,402 --> 00:26:46,571
I MEAN, PLAYING INTO HIS SENTIMENTS
IS MORE OR LESS CHEATING

719
00:26:46,638 --> 00:26:48,239
He wants to serve a warm meal.

720
00:26:48,306 --> 00:26:50,508
-The bottom compartment was for soup.
-It was.

721
00:26:50,575 --> 00:26:52,510
Moms would pack lunches in those
for school trips.

722
00:26:52,577 --> 00:26:53,945
Are you already leaning this way?

723
00:26:54,012 --> 00:26:54,846
I'm about to cry.

724
00:26:55,847 --> 00:26:57,549
Did you get lunch at school,
or did you pack lunch?

725
00:26:57,616 --> 00:26:59,351
-I've done both.
-And packed lunches?

726
00:26:59,417 --> 00:27:00,986
-Then you must have memories of them.
-Yes.

727
00:27:01,052 --> 00:27:03,021
I'm sure his mother made
these lunch boxes.

728
00:27:03,088 --> 00:27:04,956
I got lunch at school,

729
00:27:05,023 --> 00:27:06,758
but I packed dessert in a lunch box.

730
00:27:08,093 --> 00:27:10,729
So the school provided lunch,
but you brought your own food too?

731
00:27:10,795 --> 00:27:13,164
-Yes, as dessert.
-Dessert.

732
00:27:13,431 --> 00:27:15,367
3. ADD WATER, CHOPPED GARLIC,
CHEONGYANG PEPPER TO DOENJANG SOUP

733
00:27:15,433 --> 00:27:18,003
I added more water
to make it more like a soup.

734
00:27:18,069 --> 00:27:19,638
-Like soup.
-And not <i>jjigae, </i>stew<i>.</i>

735
00:27:19,704 --> 00:27:21,673
He's making <i>doenjang </i>soup<i>, </i>not <i>jjigae.</i>

736
00:27:21,740 --> 00:27:23,675
Man, a thermal lunch box sounds too good.

737
00:27:23,742 --> 00:27:24,709
Don't let him bother you.

738
00:27:25,543 --> 00:27:26,411
You got this.

739
00:27:27,312 --> 00:27:30,115
4. OIL PAN, STIR-FRY GREEN ONION, GARLIC,
SOY SAUCE, COOKING WINE, AND PORK BELLY

740
00:27:30,181 --> 00:27:31,716
She's making the pork belly stir-fry.

741
00:27:31,783 --> 00:27:33,752
That looks good. Gosh.

742
00:27:33,818 --> 00:27:35,320
IT'S THANKS TO YOUR SUPPORT

743
00:27:36,154 --> 00:27:38,323
Will that stir-fry go on top of the rice?

744
00:27:38,390 --> 00:27:39,457
Yes, it'll sit on top.

745
00:27:40,291 --> 00:27:42,994
-She seasons it in Chinese-style.
-Oyster sauce.

746
00:27:43,061 --> 00:27:45,330
She's making Hong Kong-style
stone pot rice.

747
00:27:45,397 --> 00:27:47,632
Eun-yeong's pork belly
looks really delicious.

748
00:27:47,699 --> 00:27:49,501
That already looks so good.

749
00:27:49,567 --> 00:27:50,902
Eun-yeong, the poached egg.

750
00:27:52,570 --> 00:27:54,272
She scoops out the poached egg.

751
00:27:54,339 --> 00:27:55,306
Excellent job.

752
00:27:55,373 --> 00:27:57,275
He's rolling the omelet!

753
00:27:57,342 --> 00:27:59,644
-Jong-won is rolling it!
-That's so important.

754
00:28:00,578 --> 00:28:01,780
I hope it doesn't break.

755
00:28:01,846 --> 00:28:03,281
-Don't let it rip.
-It ripped.

756
00:28:03,348 --> 00:28:04,983
-Did it rip?
-It didn't!

757
00:28:05,383 --> 00:28:07,052
WILL IT RIP?

758
00:28:07,118 --> 00:28:08,953
That's not what's important.

759
00:28:09,020 --> 00:28:12,891
When moms make rolled omelets,
they always end up looking golden.

760
00:28:12,957 --> 00:28:15,093
-You're right.
-It's quite similar so far.

761
00:28:15,794 --> 00:28:16,995
That looks good.

762
00:28:17,062 --> 00:28:18,196
He's rolling it easily.

763
00:28:18,263 --> 00:28:20,298
-He goes forward, and then backward.
-That's right.

764
00:28:20,365 --> 00:28:23,134
-It looks so pretty.
-He makes it look pretty too.

765
00:28:23,201 --> 00:28:26,805
-He's shaping it once again.
-He's shaping it.

766
00:28:26,871 --> 00:28:29,507
That was why he said
the shape wasn't important.

767
00:28:29,574 --> 00:28:32,177
You can always roll it with a mat
to maintain its shape.

768
00:28:33,244 --> 00:28:35,914
Chef Eun-yeong, are you using <i>mukeunji,</i>
aged kimchi<i>?</i>

769
00:28:35,980 --> 00:28:37,782
-Yes, it's kimchi.
-Is that another topping?

770
00:28:37,849 --> 00:28:40,585
Yes, I'm washing it to season it
before I top it over the rice.

771
00:28:40,652 --> 00:28:42,320
-That sounds good.
-That sounds good.

772
00:28:42,387 --> 00:28:43,822
Do people in Hong Kong use <i>mukeunji?</i>

773
00:28:43,888 --> 00:28:46,024
No, but today, he has to eat this

774
00:28:46,091 --> 00:28:47,292
before he passes away.

775
00:28:47,358 --> 00:28:48,393
So…

776
00:28:49,728 --> 00:28:51,963
HE'LL WANT TO EAT KOREAN FOOD
BEFORE HE PASSES

777
00:28:52,030 --> 00:28:53,798
She'll be disappointed
if I don't pass away.

778
00:28:53,865 --> 00:28:56,401
Yes, I didn't want this
to be too authentic.

779
00:28:56,468 --> 00:28:58,236
I MEAN, THE LAST MEAL
IN HONG KONG-STYLE CAN BE ODD…

780
00:28:58,303 --> 00:28:59,871
SESAME OIL, SUGAR

781
00:28:59,938 --> 00:29:01,506
She's done making <i>mukeunji.</i>

782
00:29:01,573 --> 00:29:04,309
-They only have six minutes left.
-Time is flying.

783
00:29:04,375 --> 00:29:05,410
You don't have much time.

784
00:29:05,477 --> 00:29:07,011
-Five minutes.
-Five minutes and forty-five seconds.

785
00:29:07,078 --> 00:29:09,447
-Instant rice?
-Chef Jong-won uses instant rice.

786
00:29:09,514 --> 00:29:12,350
-It's <i>gimbap</i>, so he can't help it.
-He has to do things quickly.

787
00:29:13,418 --> 00:29:14,552
The seaweed.

788
00:29:14,619 --> 00:29:16,087
-He roasts it lightly.
-He does.

789
00:29:16,154 --> 00:29:18,256
He has time to roast them?

790
00:29:18,323 --> 00:29:21,126
Do people roast dried seaweed
when they make <i>gimbap?</i>

791
00:29:21,192 --> 00:29:22,360
Most mothers don't.

792
00:29:22,427 --> 00:29:24,963
-But that makes it more savory.
-I see.

793
00:29:25,029 --> 00:29:27,599
He's about to make the <i>gimbap.</i>

794
00:29:27,665 --> 00:29:29,634
He's going to roll them. It looks pretty.

795
00:29:29,701 --> 00:29:32,470
I wanted to use lots of fillings,
and I imagined mothers would be the same.

796
00:29:32,537 --> 00:29:34,439
He's going to add many different fillings.

797
00:29:34,506 --> 00:29:36,574
-Lettuce? Perilla leaf?
-Lettuce? In <i>gimbap?</i>

798
00:29:36,641 --> 00:29:38,309
He said he liked veggie wraps.

799
00:29:38,376 --> 00:29:39,978
Veggie wraps.

800
00:29:40,044 --> 00:29:42,147
I'm moved. I do like them.

801
00:29:42,213 --> 00:29:43,148
FILLING 2: PICKLED RADISH

802
00:29:43,214 --> 00:29:45,850
-You had pickled radish.
-Picked radish… Right.

803
00:29:46,417 --> 00:29:48,520
He's not using
the ordinary kind of pickled radish.

804
00:29:48,586 --> 00:29:50,789
Those are <i>gimbap</i> for a special day.

805
00:29:50,855 --> 00:29:52,323
It's not your everyday <i>gimbap.</i>

806
00:29:52,390 --> 00:29:54,125
You'll be taking a long journey,

807
00:29:54,192 --> 00:29:56,427
so he even cooked some beef
and threw it in there too.

808
00:29:56,494 --> 00:29:58,696
That <i>gimbap </i>has so many fillings.
It looks so good.

809
00:29:58,763 --> 00:30:01,366
Yes, he's adding everything
that was in my fridge.

810
00:30:01,432 --> 00:30:03,568
-Five minutes.
-Five minutes left.

811
00:30:03,635 --> 00:30:05,837
-Sung-ju, please report from the kitchen.
-Yes?

812
00:30:05,904 --> 00:30:07,939
-Let's go, Chef Sung-jun.
-Yes.

813
00:30:08,006 --> 00:30:09,908
It's time for me to get a taste.

814
00:30:10,575 --> 00:30:12,343
KWON SUNG-JUN, YOU'RE SO ANNOYING…

815
00:30:12,610 --> 00:30:13,478
IS IT FINALLY MY TURN?

816
00:30:13,545 --> 00:30:15,547
-You must remain impartial.
-I shall.

817
00:30:15,613 --> 00:30:17,081
You cannot take someone's side.

818
00:30:17,148 --> 00:30:17,982
Let me try the soup.

819
00:30:18,049 --> 00:30:21,019
He's trying the soup, <i>doenjang </i>soup<i>.</i>

820
00:30:21,085 --> 00:30:22,554
<i>-Doenjang </i>soup.
<i>-Doenjang </i>soup?

821
00:30:22,620 --> 00:30:24,722
What do you think, Sung-jun?

822
00:30:25,089 --> 00:30:26,658
WHAT'S IT LIKE?

823
00:30:26,724 --> 00:30:27,892
It's a bit bland.

824
00:30:27,959 --> 00:30:29,894
-Is it?
-It's a bit too weak.

825
00:30:29,961 --> 00:30:31,496
-Is it?
-Is this intentional?

826
00:30:31,563 --> 00:30:33,565
-He may be lying right now.
-I'm not.

827
00:30:33,631 --> 00:30:35,633
-I'm serious.
-I think it tastes fine.

828
00:30:35,700 --> 00:30:37,368
-He's taking sides.
-He's on her side.

829
00:30:37,435 --> 00:30:40,738
-Sung-ju, can you try some?
-Let me try some.

830
00:30:40,805 --> 00:30:43,675
I have a feeling
Sung-jun is here to root for Eun-yeong.

831
00:30:43,741 --> 00:30:46,244
He might be sabotaging me,
so I will disregard it.

832
00:30:46,311 --> 00:30:48,646
Will that soup
leave no regrets in this life?

833
00:30:48,713 --> 00:30:51,049
REGRETS, IN OR OUT?

834
00:30:51,115 --> 00:30:52,951
I think regrets will remain.

835
00:30:53,518 --> 00:30:55,753
-It's bland, right?
-It's a little bland.

836
00:30:55,820 --> 00:30:56,754
Sung-jun didn't lie.

837
00:30:56,821 --> 00:30:58,489
I still have four minutes left.

838
00:30:58,556 --> 00:31:01,926
And the <i>doenjang</i> soup you eat with <i>gimbap</i>
can't be salty. It has to be bland.

839
00:31:01,993 --> 00:31:03,428
Is there anything I can try?

840
00:31:03,494 --> 00:31:04,529
LURKING AROUND EUN-YEONG

841
00:31:04,596 --> 00:31:05,830
Sung-jun, try the pork.

842
00:31:05,897 --> 00:31:06,798
-The pork?
-Yes.

843
00:31:06,865 --> 00:31:09,400
-Let me try the pork.
-The pork.

844
00:31:09,467 --> 00:31:11,135
Don't eat too much.

845
00:31:11,202 --> 00:31:13,438
-What?
-She has to eat some too.

846
00:31:13,504 --> 00:31:15,240
-It's pork belly.
-Don't take too much.

847
00:31:15,306 --> 00:31:17,141
-This is an important aspect.
-The meat, yes.

848
00:31:17,208 --> 00:31:19,277
He's trying the pork belly.

849
00:31:19,911 --> 00:31:20,745
What?

850
00:31:21,379 --> 00:31:22,547
CLAPPING

851
00:31:22,614 --> 00:31:23,982
-So?
-Impeccable.

852
00:31:24,048 --> 00:31:26,050
-Impeccable.
-Is it?

853
00:31:26,117 --> 00:31:27,385
THAT'S IT, SUNG-JUN!

854
00:31:27,452 --> 00:31:29,120
-I'm so excited.
-Hey!

855
00:31:29,454 --> 00:31:31,556
EUN-YEONG TAKES THE LEAD

856
00:31:31,890 --> 00:31:33,791
AND FINALLY…

857
00:31:34,492 --> 00:31:36,895
SHE CAN LET HIM PASS AWAY IN PEACE…

858
00:31:38,696 --> 00:31:41,833
May I pass away a little later?
It's still a bit too early.

859
00:31:41,966 --> 00:31:43,835
NOPE

860
00:31:43,902 --> 00:31:45,970
-What about the rice?
-I hope it turned out well.

861
00:31:46,037 --> 00:31:47,572
-It looks good.
-It turned out well.

862
00:31:47,639 --> 00:31:48,473
The rice.

863
00:31:48,539 --> 00:31:50,241
Isn't it too dry?

864
00:31:50,308 --> 00:31:52,810
-It's Hong Kong-style.
-Oh, is it?

865
00:31:53,211 --> 00:31:56,080
TOPPING HONG KONG-STYLE STONE POT RICE
WITH PORK BELLY!

866
00:31:56,781 --> 00:31:58,549
That looks so good.

867
00:31:58,616 --> 00:32:02,520
Chef Eun-yeong is busy making
Hong Kong-style stone pot rice.

868
00:32:02,887 --> 00:32:04,489
JONG-WON ROLLS THE GIMBAP!

869
00:32:04,555 --> 00:32:07,025
Roll it. He's rolling it.

870
00:32:07,926 --> 00:32:09,260
ROLL IT WELL

871
00:32:09,327 --> 00:32:11,262
The best kind of <i>gimbap </i>is beef <i>gimbap.</i>

872
00:32:11,329 --> 00:32:12,797
That's true.

873
00:32:12,864 --> 00:32:15,934
PUSH IT WELL

874
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:17,669
Both <i>gimbap</i> turned out nicely.

875
00:32:17,735 --> 00:32:20,305
Everything is ready,
both <i>gimbap</i> and rolled omelet.

876
00:32:20,371 --> 00:32:22,240
He's cutting the rolled omelet.

877
00:32:22,307 --> 00:32:25,109
It's the type of rolled omelet
that your mom makes.

878
00:32:25,176 --> 00:32:27,145
Rolled omelet in mom's style.

879
00:32:27,211 --> 00:32:28,813
Are you throwing those out?

880
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:30,481
-Rolled omelet!
-Rolled omelet!

881
00:32:30,548 --> 00:32:32,150
Does it taste like something a mom cooks?

882
00:32:32,216 --> 00:32:33,651
Does it taste like something a mom cooks?

883
00:32:33,718 --> 00:32:35,887
I'm thinking of my mother!

884
00:32:37,722 --> 00:32:39,857
It'd taste exactly like hers
with some ketchup.

885
00:32:40,591 --> 00:32:41,726
JUST LIKE HOW MOM WOULD PACK IT

886
00:32:41,793 --> 00:32:43,828
It's the thermal lunch box.

887
00:32:44,562 --> 00:32:45,596
I need ketchup.

888
00:32:45,663 --> 00:32:47,265
He needs ketchup!

889
00:32:48,199 --> 00:32:50,401
WON-HUN SAYS HE NEEDS KETCHUP,

890
00:32:50,902 --> 00:32:52,870
SO HE DASHES WITHOUT HESITATING

891
00:32:53,271 --> 00:32:54,939
JONG-WON FORGOT TO GRAB KETCHUP…

892
00:32:55,006 --> 00:32:55,873
You need ketchup.

893
00:32:56,708 --> 00:32:57,742
Does he have ketchup?

894
00:32:57,809 --> 00:32:58,910
DON'T WORRY, I'M ON IT

895
00:32:58,977 --> 00:33:00,278
Ketchup!

896
00:33:00,778 --> 00:33:01,646
ON MY WAY TO SQUEEZE IT OUT

897
00:33:01,713 --> 00:33:03,982
-Ketchup.
-Right here.

898
00:33:04,048 --> 00:33:05,683
HAPPY TO SEE POONG, WHO RAN OVER

899
00:33:06,484 --> 00:33:07,919
I'll put it in the corner.

900
00:33:07,986 --> 00:33:10,355
-You have 1 minute and 42 seconds.
-1 minute and 42 seconds.

901
00:33:10,655 --> 00:33:11,789
EUN-YEONG MAKES A LAST-MINUTE SAUCE

902
00:33:12,256 --> 00:33:16,094
5. MIX SOY SAUCE, WATER, SUGAR,
PERILLA OIL, AND CRUSHED GARLIC

903
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:17,528
-Is the kimchi ready?
-It's ready.

904
00:33:17,595 --> 00:33:18,830
-Just like that.
-It looks good.

905
00:33:18,896 --> 00:33:21,232
She tops the rice
with pork belly, bracken, and <i>mukeunji.</i>

906
00:33:21,299 --> 00:33:23,334
Do you have more toppings?

907
00:33:23,401 --> 00:33:24,369
-Yes, of course.
-The poached egg.

908
00:33:24,435 --> 00:33:26,270
Eun-yeong is almost done!

909
00:33:27,071 --> 00:33:28,306
A minute and thirty seconds, Jong-won.

910
00:33:28,373 --> 00:33:31,642
It's like the <i>gimbap</i> our moms would make
for special occasions.

911
00:33:31,709 --> 00:33:32,944
Now, <i>doenjang </i>soup<i>.</i>

912
00:33:33,011 --> 00:33:34,412
It continues to boil down.

913
00:33:34,479 --> 00:33:36,447
-One minute!
-One minute to go.

914
00:33:36,514 --> 00:33:37,782
The last tasting.

915
00:33:38,449 --> 00:33:40,385
-It looks good.
-Oh my!

916
00:33:40,451 --> 00:33:41,519
Has it boiled down?

917
00:33:41,586 --> 00:33:44,489
It's seasoned perfectly now.

918
00:33:44,555 --> 00:33:45,990
What's wrong? I like it.

919
00:33:46,057 --> 00:33:47,191
You're right on.

920
00:33:47,925 --> 00:33:49,227
-He's so annoying.
-Jong-won always has a plan.

921
00:33:49,293 --> 00:33:50,428
Fifty seconds!

922
00:33:50,928 --> 00:33:54,766
THE LAST TOPPING IS GREEN ONION!

923
00:33:54,832 --> 00:33:57,268
-It's an emergency.
-Is it really?

924
00:33:57,335 --> 00:33:58,436
The soup is really good.

925
00:33:58,503 --> 00:33:59,404
THE FINAL STEAMING

926
00:33:59,470 --> 00:34:00,405
The soup is delicious.

927
00:34:00,471 --> 00:34:01,706
It smells good.

928
00:34:02,774 --> 00:34:04,876
Why is that ketchup so watery?

929
00:34:04,942 --> 00:34:08,312
That's the ketchup I don't like.

930
00:34:08,379 --> 00:34:09,847
It's called vegetable ketchup.

931
00:34:09,914 --> 00:34:11,983
It's not regular tomato ketchup.

932
00:34:12,050 --> 00:34:14,385
Was there another one?

933
00:34:14,452 --> 00:34:15,720
Fifty seconds.

934
00:34:15,787 --> 00:34:17,021
BACK TO THE FRIDGE!

935
00:34:17,755 --> 00:34:19,657
I CAN'T LET HIM LOSE
BECAUSE OF THAT KETCHUP!

936
00:34:20,224 --> 00:34:21,559
DÉJÀ VU

937
00:34:21,626 --> 00:34:23,261
-It's on the right.
-The right?

938
00:34:23,361 --> 00:34:24,495
THIS ONE?

939
00:34:24,562 --> 00:34:25,863
-That's the ketchup.
-This one?

940
00:34:25,930 --> 00:34:27,265
Yes, that's it.

941
00:34:27,331 --> 00:34:29,200
I'M COMING TO SQUEEZE IT OUT AGAIN

942
00:34:29,267 --> 00:34:31,002
YOU NEED NEW KETCHUP!

943
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:33,871
He said he didn't like this ketchup.

944
00:34:33,938 --> 00:34:35,573
-I can't switch it out now.
-He doesn't like it?

945
00:34:35,640 --> 00:34:37,108
-The ketchup I don't like.
-You can do it.

946
00:34:37,175 --> 00:34:38,142
But I hate that ketchup.

947
00:34:38,209 --> 00:34:39,043
WHINING

948
00:34:39,110 --> 00:34:42,180
-That's the ketchup he doesn't like!
-Use this one instead.

949
00:34:42,246 --> 00:34:44,248
-Yes, that's it.
-Ketchup.

950
00:34:44,315 --> 00:34:46,751
-Good.
-So you have ketchup preferences?

951
00:34:46,818 --> 00:34:48,419
I prefer tomato ketchup.

952
00:34:48,753 --> 00:34:49,887
AND AS THEY SPEAK!

953
00:34:49,954 --> 00:34:51,355
Is there a big difference?

954
00:34:51,422 --> 00:34:53,858
-Fifteen seconds.
-Ten seconds.

955
00:34:53,925 --> 00:34:55,293
-Fifteen seconds.
-Ten seconds.

956
00:34:55,359 --> 00:34:56,394
Time's almost up.

957
00:34:56,461 --> 00:34:57,762
Jong-won finishes.

958
00:34:57,829 --> 00:35:01,632
-Nine, eight, seven, six…
-Nine, eight, seven, six…

959
00:35:01,699 --> 00:35:03,301
-…five, four…
-…five, four…

960
00:35:03,367 --> 00:35:04,836
-Okay. You can win.
-…three…

961
00:35:04,902 --> 00:35:06,504
-Two, one.
-…two, one.

962
00:35:06,571 --> 00:35:08,706
Eun-yeong finishes as well.

963
00:35:08,773 --> 00:35:11,175
-How do they finish right on time?
-That was amazing.

964
00:35:11,242 --> 00:35:12,510
So this is the lunch box.

965
00:35:12,577 --> 00:35:13,411
THE SENTIMENTAL 3-TIER LUNCH BOX

966
00:35:13,478 --> 00:35:14,745
-I'm excited.
-That's sentimental.

967
00:35:14,812 --> 00:35:15,913
He went all out.

968
00:35:15,980 --> 00:35:17,482
I'm already moved.

969
00:35:17,548 --> 00:35:18,850
I want to eat this one too.

970
00:35:18,916 --> 00:35:20,084
Dang it.

971
00:35:20,151 --> 00:35:21,853
-It does look good.
-Right?

972
00:35:22,987 --> 00:35:24,489
Why didn't you make it more sentimental?

973
00:35:24,555 --> 00:35:26,591
-That's really hard.
-She's not too emotional.

974
00:35:26,657 --> 00:35:29,393
-Look at those details.
-Details.

975
00:35:29,460 --> 00:35:32,864
-It's lunch for the college entrance exam.
-You're right.

976
00:35:32,930 --> 00:35:35,633
There's always a tangerine
with that kind of lunch box.

977
00:35:35,700 --> 00:35:36,834
Yes, always.

978
00:35:36,901 --> 00:35:38,202
-That and soy milk.
-Yes.

979
00:35:38,269 --> 00:35:39,670
Can you put a lemon on top?

980
00:35:41,405 --> 00:35:43,307
It would've been great
if you had time to write a note.

981
00:35:43,374 --> 00:35:46,043
"Eat this and pass away in peace."

982
00:35:46,110 --> 00:35:48,312
-With tear stains.
-"I was happy to have known you."

983
00:35:48,379 --> 00:35:49,580
"I'll never forget you."

984
00:35:49,647 --> 00:35:51,682
Both chefs finished cooking for Won-hun,

985
00:35:51,749 --> 00:35:54,886
I Mean, I Want to Eat It Before Death.

986
00:35:54,952 --> 00:35:57,855
They cooked with all seriousness,

987
00:35:57,922 --> 00:36:00,658
thinking that you're going to take
the longest journey of your life.

988
00:36:00,725 --> 00:36:03,427
-They wanted you to eat nice food.
-Don't go too far.

989
00:36:03,494 --> 00:36:05,329
-May I make an offer?
-What is it?

990
00:36:05,396 --> 00:36:08,132
Let's say Su-ji is his mom
bringing him the lunch box.

991
00:36:08,199 --> 00:36:11,435
When kids ran late for school,
moms would run after them with these.

992
00:36:11,502 --> 00:36:12,537
-I mean, you're a good actor.
-Right.

993
00:36:12,603 --> 00:36:15,273
Let's say he left his lunch box
on his college entrance exam day.

994
00:36:15,339 --> 00:36:18,075
-He forgot.
-His mom should bring it to him.

995
00:36:18,142 --> 00:36:20,945
That one should be delivered
by a Korean mom,

996
00:36:21,012 --> 00:36:22,513
and this one, by a Hong Kong mom.

997
00:36:22,580 --> 00:36:23,981
-Okay.
-It's in Hong Kong-style.

998
00:36:24,048 --> 00:36:25,316
-And put it in front of him?
-Yes.

999
00:36:25,383 --> 00:36:28,286
-Think of him as your son.
-Two characters. Please serve it to him.

1000
00:36:28,352 --> 00:36:29,954
Would it be okay if someone called

1001
00:36:30,021 --> 00:36:34,325
-while you were on your way to deliver?
-As she walks? Isn't that too much?

1002
00:36:34,392 --> 00:36:35,960
That's way too hard.

1003
00:36:36,027 --> 00:36:37,461
But she's playing along.

1004
00:36:37,528 --> 00:36:40,598
SU-JI DELIVERS A LUNCH BOX TO HER SON
AND RECEIVES A CALL

1005
00:36:40,865 --> 00:36:44,402
[CHATTERING FROM CLASSROOM]

1006
00:36:44,969 --> 00:36:46,671
THE KOREAN MOM LOOKS TROUBLED

1007
00:36:46,737 --> 00:36:48,306
He takes after his dad

1008
00:36:48,372 --> 00:36:50,441
and is so forgetful!

1009
00:36:50,508 --> 00:36:52,743
[SUNG-JU, PLAYING A PHONE] R-R-RING

1010
00:36:52,810 --> 00:36:54,879
HUBBY

1011
00:36:54,946 --> 00:36:55,880
Hello?

1012
00:36:55,947 --> 00:36:58,216
I'm busy taking Hun's lunch box to school.
I'll talk to you later.

1013
00:36:59,050 --> 00:37:00,318
Yes, I do love you!

1014
00:37:01,419 --> 00:37:03,221
-Mom!
-Hun!

1015
00:37:03,287 --> 00:37:04,622
You need to eat.

1016
00:37:04,689 --> 00:37:06,857
-I forgot.
-Wait, let me explain it to you.

1017
00:37:06,924 --> 00:37:08,392
What's more important than your exam

1018
00:37:08,459 --> 00:37:09,927
-is that there's soup at the bottom.
-Okay.

1019
00:37:09,994 --> 00:37:12,296
I put a lot of love and effort into it,

1020
00:37:12,363 --> 00:37:15,266
-so make sure you drink every drop.
-Okay, I will.

1021
00:37:15,333 --> 00:37:17,702
-And mix it with some rice too.
-Mom, the exam is ongoing.

1022
00:37:17,768 --> 00:37:18,970
-The third…
-They're taking it.

1023
00:37:19,036 --> 00:37:20,371
I'm not done yet.

1024
00:37:20,438 --> 00:37:23,641
The third one has rolled omelet,
so dip it in ketchup and eat it.

1025
00:37:23,708 --> 00:37:25,309
-It'll taste amazing.
-Okay. I got it.

1026
00:37:25,376 --> 00:37:28,412
I'm sure you'll end up getting full marks
on the entrance exam!

1027
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:30,114
Give me a moment.

1028
00:37:30,181 --> 00:37:31,649
[SUNG-JU RINGS AGAIN]

1029
00:37:32,216 --> 00:37:33,150
Hey.

1030
00:37:33,217 --> 00:37:36,087
My husband just called
and asked me to bring his lunch.

1031
00:37:36,153 --> 00:37:37,355
I'm so sorry, Teacher.

1032
00:37:37,922 --> 00:37:39,257
-Good luck!
-Thanks, Mom!

1033
00:37:39,890 --> 00:37:41,659
THE CHAMPION ENTERTAINER DELIVERS

1034
00:37:41,726 --> 00:37:43,794
-She's so good.
-She did that on the spot?

1035
00:37:44,295 --> 00:37:45,496
100% IMPROVISED

1036
00:37:45,563 --> 00:37:46,964
-How can she do that?
-That was a nice break.

1037
00:37:47,031 --> 00:37:50,434
This is Mom's lunch box
made by Chef Jong-won.

1038
00:37:52,436 --> 00:37:59,443
GIMBAP, DOENJANG SOUP, AND ROLLED OMELET
MADE WITH A MOTHER'S HEART

1039
00:38:02,947 --> 00:38:06,884
CHEF SON JONG-WON'S
YOUR SON'S TOO HOT, SORRY MOM'S LUNCH BOX

1040
00:38:08,252 --> 00:38:11,455
It looks just like how it did
in the old days.

1041
00:38:12,223 --> 00:38:13,190
It's lunchtime.

1042
00:38:13,257 --> 00:38:14,659
BRINGING BACK MEMORIES

1043
00:38:14,725 --> 00:38:16,060
You should eat even if you'll pass away.

1044
00:38:16,861 --> 00:38:18,929
-It's your last lunch box.
-That's right.

1045
00:38:18,996 --> 00:38:21,565
I mean, imagine this is your last meal.

1046
00:38:21,632 --> 00:38:23,200
-When was the last time we had this?
-Tier two.

1047
00:38:23,267 --> 00:38:25,269
-It's a three-tier lunch box.
-That's right.

1048
00:38:25,603 --> 00:38:27,138
THAT'S MOM'S LOVE!

1049
00:38:27,204 --> 00:38:29,340
-It's steaming hot.
-That's the <i>doenjang</i> soup.

1050
00:38:29,407 --> 00:38:30,775
TIER 1: HOT DOENJANG SOUP

1051
00:38:31,108 --> 00:38:32,576
WOW

1052
00:38:32,643 --> 00:38:34,779
-Rolled omelet.
-Rolled omelet, the side dish.

1053
00:38:34,845 --> 00:38:37,248
That's the kind of lunch box
your friends fawn over.

1054
00:38:37,315 --> 00:38:40,051
-It's usually rice, but it's <i>gimbap.</i>
<i>-</i>Beef <i>gimbap.</i>

1055
00:38:40,117 --> 00:38:42,186
-It's beef <i>gimbap.</i>
-There's fish cake inside too.

1056
00:38:42,253 --> 00:38:44,622
-I don't know where to begin.
-Where should he begin?

1057
00:38:44,689 --> 00:38:47,258
-I'd say <i>gimbap</i>.
<i>-Gimbap.</i>

1058
00:38:47,325 --> 00:38:48,359
I'll use a spoon.

1059
00:38:48,426 --> 00:38:51,462
Our moms don't make
these lunch boxes for us anymore,

1060
00:38:51,529 --> 00:38:53,264
but think of the old days.

1061
00:38:53,531 --> 00:38:55,266
IT LOOKS SO GOOD…

1062
00:38:55,333 --> 00:38:57,001
Will it please his appetite?

1063
00:38:57,068 --> 00:38:58,636
TAKES A HUGE BITE

1064
00:38:58,703 --> 00:39:01,672
He said he preferred <i>gimbap</i>
with less rice.

1065
00:39:01,739 --> 00:39:02,673
He tried the <i>gimbap.</i>

1066
00:39:03,874 --> 00:39:06,510
It's filled with beef and bracken.

1067
00:39:06,577 --> 00:39:07,511
SMILING

1068
00:39:08,079 --> 00:39:09,313
Mom…

1069
00:39:09,780 --> 00:39:10,881
DID IT REMIND HIM OF HIS MOM?

1070
00:39:10,948 --> 00:39:12,316
-It looks good.
-Is it good?

1071
00:39:13,150 --> 00:39:14,251
-It's really…
-Yes?

1072
00:39:14,318 --> 00:39:15,886
It's different.

1073
00:39:15,953 --> 00:39:17,221
-Different?
-It's different.

1074
00:39:17,288 --> 00:39:19,123
Is it different from store-bought <i>gimbap?</i>

1075
00:39:19,190 --> 00:39:21,125
I don't like <i>gimbap </i>with too much rice.

1076
00:39:21,192 --> 00:39:23,861
But he knew exactly what I wanted

1077
00:39:23,928 --> 00:39:27,064
and added so many fillings,
such as fish cake and beef.

1078
00:39:27,131 --> 00:39:28,699
The balance is wonderful,

1079
00:39:28,766 --> 00:39:30,601
and I love the texture of the beef.

1080
00:39:30,668 --> 00:39:34,038
Compared to beef <i>gimbap</i>
we can buy just anywhere,

1081
00:39:34,105 --> 00:39:35,973
it's on a whole different level.

1082
00:39:36,240 --> 00:39:37,541
HAPPY, SAD

1083
00:39:37,608 --> 00:39:38,476
The soup.

1084
00:39:38,542 --> 00:39:40,044
-It's <i>doenjang </i>soup.
-Yes.

1085
00:39:40,811 --> 00:39:41,645
STEAMING HOT

1086
00:39:41,712 --> 00:39:43,347
The last meal he'll eat before he passes.

1087
00:39:43,414 --> 00:39:44,682
Mom's <i>doenjang </i>soup.

1088
00:39:44,749 --> 00:39:45,816
SLURP

1089
00:39:45,883 --> 00:39:47,351
I hope it's good.

1090
00:39:48,519 --> 00:39:49,520
Gosh.

1091
00:39:50,321 --> 00:39:52,223
-It's so good.
-Is it?

1092
00:39:52,289 --> 00:39:53,858
-It's so rich.
-Right.

1093
00:39:53,924 --> 00:39:55,393
Take the ketchup on top.

1094
00:39:55,459 --> 00:39:56,660
NEXT, THE ROLLED OMELET

1095
00:39:58,429 --> 00:40:01,565
Feel the texture of the omelet
and savor its flavor.

1096
00:40:02,032 --> 00:40:03,534
I CAN'T HOLD MYSELF BACK ANYMORE!

1097
00:40:03,601 --> 00:40:06,637
Rolled omelet wasn't easy to come by
back then.

1098
00:40:06,704 --> 00:40:07,938
-His face says it all.
-It's so fluffy.

1099
00:40:09,673 --> 00:40:11,208
It's like a sponge cake.

1100
00:40:12,143 --> 00:40:15,146
I honestly love my mom's food,

1101
00:40:15,212 --> 00:40:16,614
but after trying this,

1102
00:40:16,680 --> 00:40:18,282
I realized that my mom

1103
00:40:18,349 --> 00:40:19,650
doesn't make good <i>gimbap </i>at all.

1104
00:40:20,017 --> 00:40:21,886
AN UNEXPECTEDLY DISRESPECTFUL SON…

1105
00:40:21,952 --> 00:40:24,655
-I thought he was a good son.
-Where's your respect?

1106
00:40:24,722 --> 00:40:27,625
He made <i>gimbap </i>that surpasses my mom's.

1107
00:40:27,691 --> 00:40:31,061
-I'm sorry, ma'am.
-That was how he felt after trying it.

1108
00:40:31,128 --> 00:40:33,431
The Korean mom's food tastes excellent.

1109
00:40:33,497 --> 00:40:35,232
-I see.
-Well, so far.

1110
00:40:35,299 --> 00:40:36,667
Is that so?

1111
00:40:36,734 --> 00:40:39,737
-The Hong Kong mom isn't so bad.
-He's leaning toward this side.

1112
00:40:39,804 --> 00:40:40,905
Can you do a Hong Kong mom?

1113
00:40:40,971 --> 00:40:43,908
-A Hong Kong mom?
-Is she going to do Lin Zhaoming?

1114
00:40:43,974 --> 00:40:45,476
-Lin Zhaoming?
-How will she depict her?

1115
00:40:45,543 --> 00:40:47,711
Next, please try Chef Eun-yeong's dish.

1116
00:40:47,778 --> 00:40:50,047
THE HONG KONG-STYLE STONE POT RICE
MADE BY THE HONG KONG MOM(?)

1117
00:40:51,282 --> 00:40:55,586
PORK BELLY, MUKEUNJI,
AND BRACKEN, HER PERSONAL CREATION

1118
00:40:56,787 --> 00:41:00,491
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
I MEAN, RICE IS GREAT BEFORE PASSING

1119
00:41:00,858 --> 00:41:03,928
[PEOPLE BUZZING IN HONG KONG]

1120
00:41:04,061 --> 00:41:06,831
CANTONESE-SOUNDING GIBBERISH

1121
00:41:06,897 --> 00:41:09,266
-"Keep it up, my son!"
-She's getting a phone call.

1122
00:41:09,333 --> 00:41:10,367
She got a call.

1123
00:41:10,434 --> 00:41:11,969
SOMEHOW, WE CAN ALL UNDERSTAND HER

1124
00:41:12,169 --> 00:41:13,771
THE SHTONE POHT IS COOMING

1125
00:41:13,838 --> 00:41:14,972
THE STONE POT RICE IS COMING

1126
00:41:15,039 --> 00:41:17,408
-Stone pot rice?
-She said the stone pot rice is coming.

1127
00:41:21,712 --> 00:41:23,747
Oh, nice. That's heavy.

1128
00:41:24,381 --> 00:41:26,984
SHE'S NOT THE KOREAN MOM,
BUT THE HONG KONG MOM

1129
00:41:27,284 --> 00:41:28,552
IMPRESSED

1130
00:41:28,619 --> 00:41:31,188
-Mix it up before you eat it.
-Okay.

1131
00:41:31,522 --> 00:41:33,123
ASTONISHED…

1132
00:41:33,524 --> 00:41:35,726
HER HUSBAND CALLS AGAIN

1133
00:41:37,461 --> 00:41:38,996
It's your dad.

1134
00:41:39,563 --> 00:41:41,398
GOING WILD

1135
00:41:41,765 --> 00:41:43,501
ARE ALL MOMS LIKE THIS?

1136
00:41:43,567 --> 00:41:44,635
Do Hong Kong moms do that too?

1137
00:41:44,702 --> 00:41:46,737
HUBBY? IT'S STILL LUNCHTIME

1138
00:41:46,804 --> 00:41:48,539
I JUST FED HIM STONE POT RICE

1139
00:41:48,706 --> 00:41:50,040
THE END

1140
00:41:50,107 --> 00:41:51,976
She knows the accent of a Hong Konger.

1141
00:41:52,042 --> 00:41:54,712
THE HONG KONG MOM WAS AWESOME TOO

1142
00:41:54,778 --> 00:41:56,180
GREAT JOB

1143
00:41:56,247 --> 00:41:57,515
She's the champion.

1144
00:41:57,581 --> 00:41:58,482
THANK YOU FOR THE SKIT

1145
00:41:58,682 --> 00:42:00,417
TIME TO TRY THE DISH

1146
00:42:00,484 --> 00:42:02,653
-This is the dish by the Hong Kong mom.
-Yes.

1147
00:42:02,720 --> 00:42:04,822
-It's still warm.
-Look at how it's steaming.

1148
00:42:04,889 --> 00:42:06,123
-It looks good.
-She made the rice.

1149
00:42:06,190 --> 00:42:08,559
Pour the soy sauce in
and mix it with the rice.

1150
00:42:08,626 --> 00:42:11,328
So pour the sauce into the pot.

1151
00:42:11,395 --> 00:42:14,131
A Hong Kong-style stone pot rice.

1152
00:42:14,198 --> 00:42:15,499
It looks so good.

1153
00:42:15,566 --> 00:42:18,602
Bracken, <i>mukeunji,</i>
pork belly, green onion…

1154
00:42:18,669 --> 00:42:19,503
And a poached egg.

1155
00:42:19,570 --> 00:42:20,971
That looks so good.

1156
00:42:21,038 --> 00:42:22,406
It does.

1157
00:42:22,473 --> 00:42:23,841
A HUGE SCOOP

1158
00:42:23,908 --> 00:42:26,644
-It got scorched too.
-It's scorched at the bottom.

1159
00:42:26,710 --> 00:42:28,579
-That's the best part.
-Get the bracken too.

1160
00:42:28,646 --> 00:42:29,713
The rice turned out nicely.

1161
00:42:29,780 --> 00:42:31,515
It'll taste so good once you mix it.

1162
00:42:31,582 --> 00:42:32,550
That poached egg.

1163
00:42:32,616 --> 00:42:33,651
MIXING

1164
00:42:33,717 --> 00:42:35,753
-It looks good.
-It's like stone pot bibimbap.

1165
00:42:35,819 --> 00:42:37,855
-It is.
-It looks like it.

1166
00:42:37,922 --> 00:42:39,256
It might be too salty.

1167
00:42:39,323 --> 00:42:40,691
TRYING A FEW PIECES ON THE SPOON

1168
00:42:43,294 --> 00:42:44,328
He's already smitten.

1169
00:42:45,095 --> 00:42:46,530
YOU'RE RIGHT

1170
00:42:46,597 --> 00:42:48,899
-I didn't even eat a proper bite.
-I know.

1171
00:42:48,966 --> 00:42:52,403
-<i>Mukeunji, </i>pork belly, and bracken.
-It'll hit him really hard.

1172
00:42:52,469 --> 00:42:55,906
-The egg yolk also acts as a sauce.
-It does.

1173
00:42:56,140 --> 00:42:57,641
THE 1ST PLACE IS INTRIGUED TOO

1174
00:42:58,976 --> 00:43:01,111
I should've gone first.

1175
00:43:01,946 --> 00:43:02,913
SHE'S 100% SERIOUS

1176
00:43:02,980 --> 00:43:04,515
This is torturing me.

1177
00:43:04,582 --> 00:43:07,217
-The Hong Kong-style stone pot rice.
-It looks good.

1178
00:43:07,284 --> 00:43:09,186
Everything was cooked to a T.

1179
00:43:09,253 --> 00:43:10,621
He got a good bite.

1180
00:43:10,688 --> 00:43:12,022
A HUGE BITE

1181
00:43:12,089 --> 00:43:14,592
Will it be a dish
he wants to eat before death?

1182
00:43:19,763 --> 00:43:21,098
-He already passed away.
-He did.

1183
00:43:21,165 --> 00:43:22,333
Don't forget the Korean mom.

1184
00:43:22,399 --> 00:43:24,301
-The flavor took him away.
-He's gone.

1185
00:43:24,835 --> 00:43:25,936
It's a peaceful death.

1186
00:43:26,003 --> 00:43:27,404
The flavor swept him away.

1187
00:43:27,471 --> 00:43:28,772
It must be really good.

1188
00:43:29,840 --> 00:43:31,909
TAKES ANOTHER BITE QUIETLY

1189
00:43:31,976 --> 00:43:34,144
I hope it's not too dry.

1190
00:43:34,211 --> 00:43:35,980
It would've been great if she served soup.

1191
00:43:36,046 --> 00:43:37,948
-It's so good.
-Is it?

1192
00:43:38,015 --> 00:43:39,016
ISN'T THE HONG KONG MOM GREAT TOO?

1193
00:43:39,083 --> 00:43:39,984
My gosh.

1194
00:43:40,951 --> 00:43:42,286
Things just got really difficult for me.

1195
00:43:42,353 --> 00:43:45,422
Did it? Can you taste everything?

1196
00:43:45,489 --> 00:43:48,626
<i>When we eat pork belly barbecue,</i>
<i>we grill it with some </i>mukeunji<i>, right?</i>

1197
00:43:48,692 --> 00:43:50,661
That's the initial flavor.

1198
00:43:50,728 --> 00:43:52,663
But the bracken adds a nice texture,

1199
00:43:52,730 --> 00:43:55,833
and the poached egg
helps the rice stick together.

1200
00:43:56,700 --> 00:43:57,701
It keeps it together.

1201
00:43:57,768 --> 00:43:59,870
-I see.
-And they pull on each other?

1202
00:43:59,937 --> 00:44:02,873
I also feel that scorched rice too,

1203
00:44:03,607 --> 00:44:05,209
so it adds some crunchiness.

1204
00:44:05,275 --> 00:44:06,377
SAVORY AND CRUNCHY

1205
00:44:06,443 --> 00:44:08,345
-That's what's great about stone pot rice.
-You're right.

1206
00:44:08,412 --> 00:44:10,714
He's really into bracken.

1207
00:44:11,482 --> 00:44:14,051
Won-hun must take
the longest journey of his life soon.

1208
00:44:14,118 --> 00:44:15,319
I hope you leave valiantly.

1209
00:44:15,386 --> 00:44:18,188
Why don't we let Su-ji try it first
before we continue?

1210
00:44:18,255 --> 00:44:19,523
-Okay.
-Really?

1211
00:44:19,590 --> 00:44:22,359
-Su-ji can try it first. She can't go on.
-She can't go on.

1212
00:44:22,426 --> 00:44:24,094
While you contemplate
and come to a decision,

1213
00:44:24,161 --> 00:44:25,896
-Su-ji will take a bite too.
-Okay.

1214
00:44:25,963 --> 00:44:29,066
Please try
Chef Jong-won's lunch box first.

1215
00:44:29,133 --> 00:44:30,067
Okay.

1216
00:44:30,834 --> 00:44:33,237
Su-ji may have a different opinion.

1217
00:44:34,471 --> 00:44:35,639
<i>Gimbap</i> first.

1218
00:44:35,706 --> 00:44:39,209
He filled it with beef and fish cake.

1219
00:44:39,343 --> 00:44:40,911
CURIOUS

1220
00:44:40,978 --> 00:44:44,515
She's trying everything carefully,
like a judge.

1221
00:44:45,149 --> 00:44:46,083
WIDE-EYED

1222
00:44:46,150 --> 00:44:47,184
NODDING

1223
00:44:47,251 --> 00:44:50,087
Her eyes became bigger
than when she tried the <i>gimbap.</i>

1224
00:44:50,154 --> 00:44:51,455
And the rolled omelet.

1225
00:44:51,522 --> 00:44:52,423
LASTLY, THE OMELET

1226
00:44:54,591 --> 00:44:56,060
THAT HITS THE SPOT

1227
00:44:56,126 --> 00:44:57,194
She's enjoying it.

1228
00:44:57,261 --> 00:44:59,897
Her facial expression says it all.

1229
00:45:01,465 --> 00:45:04,535
It feels like
my mom walked out of the fridge.

1230
00:45:05,235 --> 00:45:06,770
Walked out of the fridge?

1231
00:45:06,837 --> 00:45:09,039
-She suddenly showed up?
-Wait.

1232
00:45:09,106 --> 00:45:11,909
He brought out the flavor
of every single ingredient.

1233
00:45:11,975 --> 00:45:15,212
Moms know exactly where everything is
in the fridge,

1234
00:45:15,279 --> 00:45:17,014
and because they know that,

1235
00:45:17,081 --> 00:45:20,050
they can bring out
all the flavors at the same time.

1236
00:45:20,117 --> 00:45:23,554
I want to take this home
and give it to my son.

1237
00:45:24,388 --> 00:45:25,756
It's so delicious.

1238
00:45:25,823 --> 00:45:26,990
Next, the stone pot rice.

1239
00:45:27,624 --> 00:45:28,459
HEHE

1240
00:45:28,892 --> 00:45:30,894
YOU LOOK HAPPY

1241
00:45:30,961 --> 00:45:33,163
That soy sauce was another kick.

1242
00:45:33,731 --> 00:45:35,099
A BIG BITE

1243
00:45:35,165 --> 00:45:36,333
She's on another level.

1244
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:37,634
HER BITE IS ON ANOTHER LEVEL

1245
00:45:37,701 --> 00:45:39,636
-That looks good.
-How can you say no to that?

1246
00:45:39,703 --> 00:45:42,740
Su-ji tries
the Hong Kong-style stone pot rice.

1247
00:45:43,373 --> 00:45:45,175
The Hong Kong-style stone pot rice.

1248
00:45:45,242 --> 00:45:46,376
It's so good.

1249
00:45:46,443 --> 00:45:48,011
-Isn't it?
-Yeah.

1250
00:45:48,078 --> 00:45:50,013
I knew it. That's my big sis.

1251
00:45:50,080 --> 00:45:52,483
As I've gotten older,

1252
00:45:52,549 --> 00:45:54,885
I've come to learn
how to tell when the rice is good.

1253
00:45:54,952 --> 00:45:58,822
-The rice itself is important.
-It feels so good to eat "good rice."

1254
00:45:58,889 --> 00:46:02,326
Not only was the rice good in itself,

1255
00:46:02,392 --> 00:46:06,797
but it felt like I got to enjoy it
with my favorite side dishes.

1256
00:46:07,498 --> 00:46:09,767
-He'll decide, so you can keep eating.
-Yes.

1257
00:46:09,833 --> 00:46:12,035
-Yes, thank you.
-You're welcome.

1258
00:46:12,102 --> 00:46:13,303
This is hard.

1259
00:46:13,370 --> 00:46:15,973
It's time for Won-hun to think.

1260
00:46:16,039 --> 00:46:20,010
Whoever is chosen right now
will advance to the next round.

1261
00:46:20,077 --> 00:46:21,745
I thought about it really hard.

1262
00:46:21,812 --> 00:46:26,250
What would I want to eat as my last meal
before taking my final breath?

1263
00:46:26,316 --> 00:46:27,384
Which one is it?

1264
00:46:27,451 --> 00:46:29,419
And I think I've come to a conclusion.

1265
00:46:29,486 --> 00:46:30,521
-I wonder.
-All right.

1266
00:46:30,587 --> 00:46:31,922
He chose one of the two.

1267
00:46:31,989 --> 00:46:34,491
<i>Press one for Son Jong-won.</i>

1268
00:46:34,558 --> 00:46:36,360
<i>Press two for Park Eun-yeong.</i>

1269
00:46:37,161 --> 00:46:39,062
Please press the button!

1270
00:46:40,364 --> 00:46:43,267
-I pressed it.
-He pressed the button.

1271
00:46:43,333 --> 00:46:45,502
-He made his decision.
-Eun-yeong.

1272
00:46:45,569 --> 00:46:47,504
It's a nerve-racking moment.

1273
00:46:47,571 --> 00:46:50,741
Which one of the two
will advance to the next round?

1274
00:46:50,808 --> 00:46:53,243
-Who'll become Poong's opponent?
-Please let it be Eun-yeong.

1275
00:46:53,310 --> 00:46:55,779
-Let's find out his decision.
-No, it's obviously Chef Jong-won.

1276
00:46:55,846 --> 00:46:57,314
-Show us!
-No, it's Eun-yeong.

1277
00:46:57,381 --> 00:46:59,249
-Good work, Eun-yeong.
-No, it's her.

1278
00:46:59,316 --> 00:47:01,084
-It's Jong-won.
-The road to the championship.

1279
00:47:01,151 --> 00:47:02,953
A round between fourth and fifth place.

1280
00:47:03,020 --> 00:47:04,888
-On fourth, Eun-yeong. Fifth, Jong-won.
-It's Eun-yeong.

1281
00:47:04,955 --> 00:47:07,658
-No, it's Chef Jong-won.
-I Mean, I Want to Eat It Before Death!

1282
00:47:07,724 --> 00:47:08,792
Who won?

1283
00:47:09,493 --> 00:47:10,761
Is it Son Jong-won?

1284
00:47:11,962 --> 00:47:13,163
Or is it Park Eun-yeong?

1285
00:47:14,164 --> 00:47:15,732
Who did he choose?

1286
00:47:16,466 --> 00:47:18,035
-Which one is it?
-Eun-yeong.

1287
00:47:18,101 --> 00:47:19,069
Who did Won-hun choose?

1288
00:47:19,136 --> 00:47:19,970
GULP

1289
00:47:20,037 --> 00:47:21,772
Is it Park Eun-yeong?

1290
00:47:21,839 --> 00:47:23,073
Or is it Son Jong-won?

1291
00:47:24,408 --> 00:47:25,309
Who'll advance?

1292
00:47:25,375 --> 00:47:26,977
PARK EUN-YEONG WINS

1293
00:47:27,644 --> 00:47:30,714
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
I MEAN, RICE IS GREAT BEFORE PASSING WINS

1294
00:47:30,781 --> 00:47:32,983
-Eun-yeong wins!
-Good work.

1295
00:47:33,050 --> 00:47:34,418
Eun-yeong was chosen!

1296
00:47:34,484 --> 00:47:36,153
Just as I expected.

1297
00:47:36,220 --> 00:47:38,622
Gosh, Jong-won has been eliminated.

1298
00:47:38,689 --> 00:47:41,091
PARK EUN-YEONG VS. KIM POONG

1299
00:47:41,158 --> 00:47:42,759
It seemed like Jong-won would win.

1300
00:47:42,826 --> 00:47:45,529
-That was a huge twist.
-It really was.

1301
00:47:45,596 --> 00:47:47,130
When I had the stone pot rice,

1302
00:47:47,197 --> 00:47:49,733
the more I had it,
the better and better it tasted,

1303
00:47:49,800 --> 00:47:51,568
and I got to experience different flavors.

1304
00:47:51,635 --> 00:47:53,270
It was also as she said.

1305
00:47:53,337 --> 00:47:55,239
The rice itself was so good.

1306
00:47:55,305 --> 00:47:56,773
-Of course.
-It was so good.

1307
00:47:56,840 --> 00:48:01,245
The texture of the rice
was really a huge part of my decision.

1308
00:48:01,812 --> 00:48:03,947
-Koreans thrive on rice.
-Yes.

1309
00:48:04,014 --> 00:48:08,218
Chef Jong-won's dish
touched my heart on a deeper level.

1310
00:48:08,785 --> 00:48:09,853
But on the other hand,

1311
00:48:09,920 --> 00:48:11,622
my mom isn't this good a cook.

1312
00:48:12,189 --> 00:48:13,690
I MEAN, THAT'S TRUE…

1313
00:48:13,757 --> 00:48:16,894
So it was hard to make that connection.

1314
00:48:16,960 --> 00:48:18,962
But it was a delicious dish.

1315
00:48:19,696 --> 00:48:22,399
I've never been a particularly good son,

1316
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:26,303
but my mother was happier than anyone
when I began to appear on this show.

1317
00:48:27,738 --> 00:48:29,573
As I looked through his fridge…

1318
00:48:29,907 --> 00:48:31,375
WHAT HAVE I DONE?

1319
00:48:31,441 --> 00:48:32,542
Mom!

1320
00:48:32,609 --> 00:48:36,613
When I was younger, I didn't appreciate
the side dishes my mom used to make,

1321
00:48:36,680 --> 00:48:38,148
-but I began to like them as I aged.
-Of course.

1322
00:48:38,215 --> 00:48:40,918
-It comes with age.
-I realized it much later.

1323
00:48:40,984 --> 00:48:43,620
We're all getting emotional,
but Su-ji is still eating.

1324
00:48:43,921 --> 00:48:46,123
I EAT GIMBAP
WHEN I'M SAD…

1325
00:48:46,189 --> 00:48:47,858
Thank you for enjoying it.

1326
00:48:47,925 --> 00:48:49,526
It was a difficult decision,

1327
00:48:49,593 --> 00:48:52,496
but in the end,
Chef Eun-yeong advances to the next round!

1328
00:48:53,430 --> 00:48:56,667
-Congratulations!
-You'll go against Kim Poong.

1329
00:48:56,733 --> 00:48:59,136
-No, you aren't getting a star.
-Oh, that's right.

1330
00:48:59,202 --> 00:49:00,671
EMBARRASSED

1331
00:49:00,737 --> 00:49:02,239
It's really good.

1332
00:49:02,306 --> 00:49:04,107
They were both so delicious.

1333
00:49:04,174 --> 00:49:06,109
-This is crazy.
-Look at that!

1334
00:49:06,176 --> 00:49:07,778
-I get why she won.
-I shouldn't have eaten.

1335
00:49:08,045 --> 00:49:09,346
HOW CUTE

1336
00:49:09,913 --> 00:49:11,348
DEVOURING

1337
00:49:11,415 --> 00:49:12,449
HAPPY

1338
00:49:12,516 --> 00:49:13,817
It's really good, right?

1339
00:49:14,685 --> 00:49:16,286
SLURP

1340
00:49:17,087 --> 00:49:18,989
Can we do this?
We aren't even cooking today.

1341
00:49:20,023 --> 00:49:21,091
It's the least we can do.

1342
00:49:21,158 --> 00:49:22,192
AND THEY CONTINUED TO EAT

1343
00:49:22,259 --> 00:49:26,229
<i>The second round with ingredients</i>
<i>found in Won-hun's fridge.</i>

1344
00:49:26,296 --> 00:49:29,733
<i>It's now round two</i>

1345
00:49:29,800 --> 00:49:32,369
<i>of the 2025 </i>Chef & My Fridge<i> Championship.</i>

1346
00:49:32,436 --> 00:49:36,073
The show's one and only knockoff chef,
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong,

1347
00:49:36,139 --> 00:49:38,675
meets Chef Park Eun-yeong,

1348
00:49:38,742 --> 00:49:40,510
who won against Jong-won in round one.

1349
00:49:40,577 --> 00:49:42,646
-She's on a roll.
-Well, during the break,

1350
00:49:42,713 --> 00:49:45,282
we heard someone in the green room
say something like this.

1351
00:49:45,349 --> 00:49:48,485
"The next round is like a bonus stage."

1352
00:49:48,552 --> 00:49:50,787
"Poong is obviously going to lose."

1353
00:49:51,321 --> 00:49:55,592
The chefs all agreed to these statements.

1354
00:49:55,659 --> 00:49:58,028
It's a break for Eun-yeong.

1355
00:49:58,095 --> 00:49:59,429
Among many chefs,

1356
00:49:59,496 --> 00:50:01,064
only one of them

1357
00:50:01,565 --> 00:50:04,668
-expected Poong to win.
-What? Who is it?

1358
00:50:04,735 --> 00:50:06,770
It was Chef Nam-no.

1359
00:50:06,837 --> 00:50:10,173
I've never won against him
the entire year.

1360
00:50:10,240 --> 00:50:13,443
-Kim Poong is a tough contestant.
-So he's not easy to beat?

1361
00:50:13,510 --> 00:50:14,444
It's not that he's weak.

1362
00:50:14,511 --> 00:50:16,046
I hope he proves

1363
00:50:16,113 --> 00:50:18,482
that I wasn't weak,
but that he was just too strong.

1364
00:50:18,548 --> 00:50:20,484
He thinks Eun-yeong
will also have a tough time.

1365
00:50:20,550 --> 00:50:22,753
We've been hearing
these groundless statements,

1366
00:50:22,819 --> 00:50:24,087
but I also believe in Poong.

1367
00:50:24,154 --> 00:50:26,523
CERTAIN THAT POONG WILL WIN

1368
00:50:26,590 --> 00:50:29,760
-This is love.
-Chef Jong-won is with him too.

1369
00:50:29,826 --> 00:50:31,461
-All right.
-And one more piece of data.

1370
00:50:31,528 --> 00:50:33,296
Poong

1371
00:50:33,363 --> 00:50:36,133
participated in two rounds
with beer snacks as the theme

1372
00:50:36,199 --> 00:50:38,368
and won both times.

1373
00:50:38,435 --> 00:50:39,269
THE BEER SNACK SPECIALIST

1374
00:50:39,336 --> 00:50:42,439
However, between these two,

1375
00:50:42,506 --> 00:50:44,975
Chef Eun-yeong has never lost.

1376
00:50:45,042 --> 00:50:47,177
-I knew it.
-Three rounds, three wins.

1377
00:50:47,244 --> 00:50:50,147
When I first met Nam-no,

1378
00:50:50,213 --> 00:50:51,948
I wondered,
"Is he really a Cooking Maniac?"

1379
00:50:52,015 --> 00:50:54,084
And it turned out
that he was a fake maniac.

1380
00:50:54,151 --> 00:50:55,986
-He faked it.
-His lunacy was faked.

1381
00:50:56,053 --> 00:50:58,655
But the more I get to know Eun-yeong…

1382
00:50:58,722 --> 00:50:59,923
-The true madwoman.
-Yes, she's really…

1383
00:50:59,990 --> 00:51:01,124
SHE'S THE REAL DEAL!

1384
00:51:01,191 --> 00:51:03,427
-The real maniac.
-The real maniac.

1385
00:51:03,493 --> 00:51:06,029
-The real maniac.
-And she looks so normal too.

1386
00:51:06,096 --> 00:51:08,465
-She seems actually mad…
-She's not normal.

1387
00:51:08,532 --> 00:51:10,700
-…so I feel like…
-No, I'm not like that.

1388
00:51:10,767 --> 00:51:13,737
So I feel like
I get swept away by her mad spirit.

1389
00:51:13,804 --> 00:51:15,238
-Just like me.
-As you said,

1390
00:51:15,305 --> 00:51:18,775
we've competed against each other
three times already.

1391
00:51:18,842 --> 00:51:23,713
So I consider this round
to be a short break for me.

1392
00:51:23,780 --> 00:51:26,216
-She must rest to go far.
-A break before your next round?

1393
00:51:26,283 --> 00:51:28,785
I will make sure that after this round,

1394
00:51:28,852 --> 00:51:31,221
she rests for good.

1395
00:51:33,757 --> 00:51:35,258
-He'll give you a full rest.
-That's right.

1396
00:51:36,093 --> 00:51:38,528
WEBTOON ARTIST POONG'S INGREDIENTS:
NAPA CABBAGE, SHRIMP, BREADCRUMBS,

1397
00:51:38,595 --> 00:51:40,597
LEMON, KETCHUP, CHICKEN STOCK,
COOKING CREAM, PERILLA LEAF

1398
00:51:40,664 --> 00:51:42,432
Here's the name of my dish.

1399
00:51:43,033 --> 00:51:44,968
Master Napa Cabbage, Master Poong.

1400
00:51:45,035 --> 00:51:47,204
-"Master Napa Cabbage, Master Poong."
-"Master Napa Cabbage, Master Poong."

1401
00:51:47,270 --> 00:51:49,406
-Are you using napa cabbage?
-That's right.

1402
00:51:49,473 --> 00:51:53,610
I plan to deep-fry
shrimp and napa cabbage together.

1403
00:51:53,677 --> 00:51:56,079
-Can you deep-fry napa cabbage?
-I'm curious.

1404
00:51:56,146 --> 00:51:58,381
-He even deep-fried a melon.
-That's true.

1405
00:51:58,448 --> 00:52:00,817
-What won't he deep-fry?
-Napa cabbage is often eaten as <i>jeon</i>,

1406
00:52:00,884 --> 00:52:03,687
but I thought it'd be delicious
when it's deep-fried.

1407
00:52:03,753 --> 00:52:05,055
-I see.
-So that was the idea.

1408
00:52:05,122 --> 00:52:09,392
It'll also taste fresher
than eating regular fried shrimp.

1409
00:52:09,459 --> 00:52:11,161
I also prepared two sauces
because you said

1410
00:52:11,228 --> 00:52:14,498
-you enjoy different flavors with beer.
-Yes.

1411
00:52:15,799 --> 00:52:17,868
CHEF EUN-YEONG'S INGREDIENTS:
BEEF TENDERLOIN, BREAD, MAYONNAISE,

1412
00:52:17,934 --> 00:52:20,203
MUSTARD, WASABI, BAGEL SEASONING,
MAPLE SYRUP, PICKLES, SUN-DRIED TOMATO

1413
00:52:20,270 --> 00:52:22,439
The name of my dish is

1414
00:52:22,506 --> 00:52:24,608
Kim Poong? So Relieved.

1415
00:52:25,475 --> 00:52:28,311
-"Kim Poong? So Relieved."
-It's Poong, so she's relieved.

1416
00:52:28,378 --> 00:52:30,714
I felt relieved,

1417
00:52:30,780 --> 00:52:33,617
so I want to use tenderloin
to make cube steak

1418
00:52:33,683 --> 00:52:36,520
-and serve with deep-fried bread.
-It sounds so good.

1419
00:52:36,586 --> 00:52:39,523
-It's a dish that goes well with beer.
-Yes, it already sounds good.

1420
00:52:39,589 --> 00:52:41,892
I'll also make my personal sauce

1421
00:52:41,958 --> 00:52:44,427
-to add a nice balance to the dish.
-Her personal sauce.

1422
00:52:44,494 --> 00:52:46,596
-You're playing two rounds in a row.
-I am.

1423
00:52:46,663 --> 00:52:47,564
Are you not tired?

1424
00:52:47,631 --> 00:52:50,100
-I'm fine so far.
-You are? Good.

1425
00:52:50,467 --> 00:52:53,003
FINALLY!

1426
00:52:53,170 --> 00:52:54,437
ANXIOUS

1427
00:52:54,504 --> 00:52:56,740
2025 <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> Championship.

1428
00:52:56,806 --> 00:52:58,975
Let us begin round two.

1429
00:52:59,042 --> 00:53:02,846
She has already struck Poong out,

1430
00:53:02,913 --> 00:53:05,282
so she'll now make him leave the game.

1431
00:53:05,348 --> 00:53:07,784
Successful Maniac, Chef Park Eun-yeong.

1432
00:53:08,818 --> 00:53:11,488
No, he's the real maniac of the show.

1433
00:53:11,555 --> 00:53:13,156
THE REAL MANIAC WHO'LL STOP SUC-MAN!

1434
00:53:13,223 --> 00:53:15,292
A man who wishes to present
the craziest dishes,

1435
00:53:15,358 --> 00:53:18,228
a regular old maniac,
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong.

1436
00:53:18,295 --> 00:53:21,064
Who'll advance to the third round?

1437
00:53:21,131 --> 00:53:23,533
Who's going to go against Chef Ho-young?

1438
00:53:23,600 --> 00:53:25,936
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1439
00:53:26,002 --> 00:53:28,104
-You can do this!
-Let's go!

1440
00:53:28,738 --> 00:53:31,041
ROUND 2 BEGINS!

1441
00:53:31,107 --> 00:53:32,409
REGULAR SEASON 3RD PLACE
KIM POONG

1442
00:53:32,475 --> 00:53:33,877
REGULAR SEASON 4TH PLACE
PARK EUN-YEONG

1443
00:53:33,944 --> 00:53:34,878
Is that tenderloin?

1444
00:53:34,945 --> 00:53:36,513
-It is.
-She said she'd make steak,

1445
00:53:36,580 --> 00:53:38,315
but she's cutting the meat into cubes.

1446
00:53:38,381 --> 00:53:39,316
Cube steak.

1447
00:53:39,382 --> 00:53:41,985
Won-hun already knows what she's making.

1448
00:53:42,052 --> 00:53:44,354
Tenderloin is my favorite beef cut.

1449
00:53:45,388 --> 00:53:47,457
-What a relief.
-Yes, it's cube steak.

1450
00:53:47,524 --> 00:53:49,492
Are you okay with eating cube steak?

1451
00:53:49,559 --> 00:53:50,827
-It sounds wonderful.
-Right.

1452
00:53:50,894 --> 00:53:52,395
Because it's bite-sized?

1453
00:53:52,462 --> 00:53:53,997
1. SEASON CUBED TENDERLOIN
WITH SOY SAUCE, PEPPER, AND COOKING WINE

1454
00:53:54,064 --> 00:53:56,032
Judging only by the explanations,

1455
00:53:56,099 --> 00:53:58,768
I'm more excited for
Chef Eun-yeong's dish.

1456
00:53:59,803 --> 00:54:00,804
I see.

1457
00:54:00,870 --> 00:54:03,340
This is the second round,
so the winner of this round

1458
00:54:03,406 --> 00:54:05,075
will go against Chef Ho-young.

1459
00:54:05,141 --> 00:54:06,309
ALSO NERVOUS

1460
00:54:06,376 --> 00:54:08,612
Poong begins with his usual chili oil.

1461
00:54:08,678 --> 00:54:11,514
Different from usual,
he's been checking the temperature.

1462
00:54:11,581 --> 00:54:12,515
<i>He's never done that before.</i>

1463
00:54:12,749 --> 00:54:14,851
POONG IS SERIOUS TODAY TOO!

1464
00:54:14,918 --> 00:54:17,387
He's working with the napa cabbage.
Master Napa Cabbage, Master Poong.

1465
00:54:17,454 --> 00:54:21,124
He's beating the napa cabbage
to flatten it widely.

1466
00:54:21,191 --> 00:54:23,059
Why is he beating the napa cabbage?

1467
00:54:23,126 --> 00:54:27,197
-It's bent, so he wants to make it flat.
-To flatten it.

1468
00:54:27,264 --> 00:54:30,934
He mixes frying powder, water, and starch.

1469
00:54:35,005 --> 00:54:36,072
SERIOUS

1470
00:54:36,139 --> 00:54:38,408
-It doesn't feel like a show today.
-Eun-yeong is so serious.

1471
00:54:38,475 --> 00:54:41,478
Don't push through so tenaciously.
I'm too intimidated to talk to you.

1472
00:54:42,545 --> 00:54:43,380
ADDING EGG TO SEASONED, CUBED STEAK?

1473
00:54:43,446 --> 00:54:45,782
It looks like Chef Eun-yeong
is seasoning the tenderloin.

1474
00:54:45,849 --> 00:54:47,851
You're right. It's the Chinese style.

1475
00:54:47,917 --> 00:54:49,886
I made the batter with starch
and slightly coated the meat in it.

1476
00:54:49,953 --> 00:54:51,087
She added cooking oil.

1477
00:54:51,154 --> 00:54:54,024
You mix it with cooking oil
and par-fry it in hot oil,

1478
00:54:54,090 --> 00:54:55,425
and it makes the meat very tender.

1479
00:54:55,492 --> 00:54:56,826
CHINESE METHOD OF TENDERIZING MEAT

1480
00:54:56,893 --> 00:54:59,696
Eun-yeong fries the seasoned tenderloin!

1481
00:54:59,763 --> 00:55:00,997
2. MIX EGG, STARCH, AND OIL WITH MEAT
AND PAR-FRY IN HOT OIL

1482
00:55:01,598 --> 00:55:03,333
Poong needs to step it up.

1483
00:55:03,400 --> 00:55:04,467
RESTING AFTER FRYING

1484
00:55:06,303 --> 00:55:09,806
Poong has spread out the batter.

1485
00:55:09,873 --> 00:55:12,142
He must be using a huge tray
because he's using napa cabbage.

1486
00:55:12,208 --> 00:55:14,311
That was the first time Sam talked today.

1487
00:55:15,011 --> 00:55:16,613
-The second.
-That was the first time.

1488
00:55:16,680 --> 00:55:20,083
Once, Sam called Poong out
for always making similar dishes,

1489
00:55:20,150 --> 00:55:21,885
but Poong came back
with an excellent point.

1490
00:55:21,951 --> 00:55:23,153
-What did he say?
-"So what?"

1491
00:55:23,219 --> 00:55:25,188
"The dishes might be similar,
but the guests are different."

1492
00:55:26,856 --> 00:55:28,258
THE INSIGHT OF 3RD PLACE

1493
00:55:28,325 --> 00:55:30,293
-That's true.
-The guests are always new.

1494
00:55:30,360 --> 00:55:33,797
He knows exactly how this show works.

1495
00:55:33,863 --> 00:55:36,232
"To the guests,
my dishes are always new and fresh."

1496
00:55:36,299 --> 00:55:37,634
He can't crush the shrimp.

1497
00:55:37,701 --> 00:55:39,169
They aren't getting crushed.

1498
00:55:39,235 --> 00:55:40,303
-They aren't.
-They're the same.

1499
00:55:40,370 --> 00:55:41,871
You're crushing them before deep-frying?

1500
00:55:41,938 --> 00:55:44,074
-Damn it.
-He's crushing the shrimp.

1501
00:55:44,140 --> 00:55:48,011
Chef Yeon-bok slams on the shrimp
and turns them into balls, right?

1502
00:55:48,078 --> 00:55:49,512
I think that's what he wanted to do,

1503
00:55:49,579 --> 00:55:51,014
but I don't think it's working.

1504
00:55:51,081 --> 00:55:53,516
-They keep getting pushed.
-Yes.

1505
00:55:53,583 --> 00:55:54,684
It's as if he's skating.

1506
00:55:54,751 --> 00:55:56,419
It isn't an easy skill to pull off.

1507
00:55:56,486 --> 00:55:57,854
-It's working.
-He's pushing it down now.

1508
00:55:57,921 --> 00:56:00,924
-It still turned out nicely.
-It worked.

1509
00:56:00,990 --> 00:56:04,527
It looks like Chef Eun-yeong
is making a delicious sauce.

1510
00:56:04,594 --> 00:56:06,629
Is that the personal sauce you mentioned?

1511
00:56:06,696 --> 00:56:09,799
-Yes, it's my personal sauce.
-Mayo, wasabi, and mustard.

1512
00:56:09,866 --> 00:56:11,701
-I see.
-And she added maple syrup.

1513
00:56:11,768 --> 00:56:13,370
With those ingredients, it has to be good.

1514
00:56:13,937 --> 00:56:15,472
-I love the color.
-It's her personal sauce.

1515
00:56:15,538 --> 00:56:17,440
-Yes.
-It's been four minutes.

1516
00:56:17,507 --> 00:56:19,209
Four minutes.

1517
00:56:19,275 --> 00:56:22,312
It looks like he wants to make
shrimp balls.

1518
00:56:22,379 --> 00:56:23,646
He continues to crush them.

1519
00:56:23,713 --> 00:56:25,148
But not minced.

1520
00:56:25,215 --> 00:56:26,750
But it's not minced?

1521
00:56:26,816 --> 00:56:28,151
-I guess he wants to maintain texture.
-The texture?

1522
00:56:28,218 --> 00:56:29,919
He'll keep some texture.

1523
00:56:30,153 --> 00:56:31,054
TAP TAP

1524
00:56:31,121 --> 00:56:32,155
Egg white.

1525
00:56:32,222 --> 00:56:33,423
Yes, egg white.

1526
00:56:33,490 --> 00:56:35,692
-He's using just the egg white.
-He uses just the egg white.

1527
00:56:35,759 --> 00:56:37,927
-Are you not allowed to use the yolk?
-No.

1528
00:56:37,994 --> 00:56:40,196
-What's the reason?
-That's how everyone does it.

1529
00:56:42,799 --> 00:56:43,666
That's so true.

1530
00:56:43,867 --> 00:56:46,236
I WANT A CHARACTER LIKE THAT

1531
00:56:46,302 --> 00:56:48,037
Don't forget. He's a webtoon artist.

1532
00:56:48,104 --> 00:56:49,205
Yes, that's right.

1533
00:56:49,272 --> 00:56:51,007
He's a webtoon artist
who learned to cook by watching.

1534
00:56:51,074 --> 00:56:52,375
"That's how everyone does it."

1535
00:56:52,442 --> 00:56:54,043
You should add some starch.

1536
00:56:54,844 --> 00:56:56,379
FOLLOWS HIS ADVICE RIGHT AWAY

1537
00:56:56,880 --> 00:56:58,715
SHRIMP PASTE IS READY!

1538
00:56:59,816 --> 00:57:00,950
Chef Eun-yeong picks up bread.

1539
00:57:01,017 --> 00:57:03,253
Yes, I'll deep-fry it
and serve it on the side.

1540
00:57:03,319 --> 00:57:06,423
That's not regular bread though.
It contains a lot of butter.

1541
00:57:06,489 --> 00:57:08,525
I'm sure it'll taste more buttery
and delicious.

1542
00:57:08,591 --> 00:57:10,493
Are you not using the crusts?

1543
00:57:10,560 --> 00:57:13,696
I want him to enjoy
the soft yet crunchy texture,

1544
00:57:13,763 --> 00:57:15,131
so I'm removing the crusts.

1545
00:57:15,198 --> 00:57:17,467
It looks like the thickness is even too.

1546
00:57:17,534 --> 00:57:20,003
Look at how she's shaving it off.

1547
00:57:20,069 --> 00:57:21,805
-My gosh.
-She delivers.

1548
00:57:21,871 --> 00:57:23,306
That's my big sis.

1549
00:57:23,373 --> 00:57:24,808
You're kind of cool today.

1550
00:57:25,375 --> 00:57:26,576
-Do I seem cool today?
-Yes.

1551
00:57:26,643 --> 00:57:27,944
GODDESS OF CHINESE CUISINE

1552
00:57:28,011 --> 00:57:28,978
Nam-no.

1553
00:57:30,013 --> 00:57:31,548
-The crusts.
-The crusts?

1554
00:57:31,614 --> 00:57:33,917
Su-ji just asked for the leftover crusts.

1555
00:57:33,983 --> 00:57:35,151
Here, Su-ji.

1556
00:57:37,887 --> 00:57:40,423
NAM-NO, YOU LOOK HAPPY

1557
00:57:41,057 --> 00:57:42,225
HALF FOR SU-JI

1558
00:57:42,459 --> 00:57:44,127
HALF FOR NAM-NO

1559
00:57:45,829 --> 00:57:47,096
THE CRUSTS I ATE

1560
00:57:47,163 --> 00:57:49,999
DID NOT MAKE ME FULL

1561
00:57:50,066 --> 00:57:51,534
Please watch as you eat the crusts.

1562
00:57:51,601 --> 00:57:52,969
I'm sorry, but are you here to watch TV?

1563
00:57:53,036 --> 00:57:54,137
-It's a lot of fun.
-Is it?

1564
00:57:54,204 --> 00:57:55,939
This is why the show lasted this long.

1565
00:57:57,640 --> 00:57:59,242
4. DEEP FRY THE CRUSTLESS BREAD

1566
00:57:59,309 --> 00:58:00,910
Nine minutes left.

1567
00:58:00,977 --> 00:58:04,147
-That's how he'll deep-fry it.
-He coated the napa cabbage in the batter.

1568
00:58:04,214 --> 00:58:07,584
It'll be like the deep-fried version
of napa cabbage <i>jeon</i>.

1569
00:58:07,650 --> 00:58:09,452
He's adding shrimp on top.

1570
00:58:09,519 --> 00:58:12,322
-He's adding shrimp.
-That looks good.

1571
00:58:12,388 --> 00:58:14,057
-That looks good!
-What?

1572
00:58:14,123 --> 00:58:16,960
-That's so new.
-We didn't expect him to do this.

1573
00:58:17,026 --> 00:58:19,262
-It'll go well with beer.
-Yes.

1574
00:58:19,329 --> 00:58:20,663
That actually makes sense.

1575
00:58:20,730 --> 00:58:24,200
It looks like he'll deep-fry
the whole thing.

1576
00:58:24,267 --> 00:58:25,802
-I'm intrigued.
-Like shrimp cutlets?

1577
00:58:25,869 --> 00:58:27,403
-Like that?
-Right.

1578
00:58:27,470 --> 00:58:29,606
-The temperature is too low.
-That's not enough oil.

1579
00:58:29,672 --> 00:58:31,641
-No, the temperature is fine.
-That's not a lot of oil.

1580
00:58:31,708 --> 00:58:33,309
-It's because it's napa cabbage.
-It doesn't sink all the way.

1581
00:58:33,376 --> 00:58:35,745
-Shouldn't it make a sizzling sound?
-He's using low heat.

1582
00:58:35,812 --> 00:58:37,347
I wonder how it'll taste.

1583
00:58:37,413 --> 00:58:39,115
When you cook napa cabbage in oil,

1584
00:58:39,182 --> 00:58:41,184
it brings out the texture
and a refreshing taste, so it's nice.

1585
00:58:41,251 --> 00:58:42,585
NAPA CABBAGES GO WELL WITH OIL

1586
00:58:42,652 --> 00:58:44,287
The two are deep-frying in different ways.

1587
00:58:44,354 --> 00:58:46,523
Chef Eun-yeong deep-fries bread.

1588
00:58:46,589 --> 00:58:47,790
That looks so good.

1589
00:58:47,857 --> 00:58:49,959
It must be quite greasy.

1590
00:58:50,026 --> 00:58:51,561
Eun-yeong, you must focus.

1591
00:58:51,628 --> 00:58:54,030
-He made something crazy.
-The bread must've absorbed a lot of oil.

1592
00:58:54,097 --> 00:58:55,665
-He did something unusual again.
-Don't make it greasy.

1593
00:58:55,732 --> 00:58:57,934
The bread may be too greasy.

1594
00:58:58,001 --> 00:59:01,538
Poong deep-fries a large piece,
and it almost looks like a cutlet.

1595
00:59:01,604 --> 00:59:02,872
Most chefs

1596
00:59:02,939 --> 00:59:06,075
would have wrapped it
or secured it with something.

1597
00:59:06,142 --> 00:59:07,744
I've never seen anyone cook like him.

1598
00:59:07,810 --> 00:59:10,513
And look. He's pouring oil on top.

1599
00:59:10,580 --> 00:59:12,015
-It's a high-level technique.
-He's never done it.

1600
00:59:12,081 --> 00:59:13,182
It's like basting.

1601
00:59:13,249 --> 00:59:14,250
Did you just say basting?

1602
00:59:14,317 --> 00:59:15,652
BASTING: POURING FRAGRANT OIL ON TOP
TO ADD FLAVOR

1603
00:59:15,718 --> 00:59:18,521
-Why are you doing that?
-It's to make the breadcrumbs stay.

1604
00:59:18,588 --> 00:59:20,123
-I'll flip it now.
-I see.

1605
00:59:20,189 --> 00:59:21,791
-Now?
-I can flip it now.

1606
00:59:21,858 --> 00:59:24,327
Yes, now that the whole thing
is sticking together.

1607
00:59:24,394 --> 00:59:26,396
HE COULDN'T FLIP IT

1608
00:59:26,462 --> 00:59:27,630
It won't flip.

1609
00:59:27,697 --> 00:59:28,631
The chopsticks don't work.

1610
00:59:28,698 --> 00:59:30,700
You can just use a spatula.

1611
00:59:31,434 --> 00:59:32,802
A BEAUTIFUL COLOR!

1612
00:59:32,869 --> 00:59:35,371
It looks good!
It has the color of scorched rice!

1613
00:59:35,438 --> 00:59:37,073
-It looks so good.
-Seven minutes!

1614
00:59:37,140 --> 00:59:38,241
It looks like a Pikachu pork cutlet.

1615
00:59:38,308 --> 00:59:40,510
Yes, it really does.

1616
00:59:40,577 --> 00:59:42,378
Wait, it won't be easy to win.

1617
00:59:43,212 --> 00:59:45,481
-What's that, Eun-yeong?
-Pickles?

1618
00:59:45,548 --> 00:59:47,584
The one he got at a department store.

1619
00:59:47,650 --> 00:59:49,586
The way she chops is pure art.

1620
00:59:50,019 --> 00:59:51,187
A CHOP-OFF!

1621
00:59:51,254 --> 00:59:52,255
CHINESE KNIFE VS CHINESE KNIFE

1622
00:59:52,322 --> 00:59:54,791
They're both using Chinese knives,
but there's a bit of a difference.

1623
00:59:55,592 --> 00:59:56,593
Poong is quite fast.

1624
00:59:56,659 --> 00:59:58,895
The sound is similar,
but the thickness is different.

1625
00:59:58,962 --> 01:00:00,029
They're so different.

1626
01:00:00,096 --> 01:00:01,197
Completely different.

1627
01:00:01,264 --> 01:00:02,565
The knives are the same brand.

1628
01:00:02,832 --> 01:00:05,101
SAME KNIFE, DIFFERENT RESULTS

1629
01:00:05,168 --> 01:00:07,604
The car may be the same,
but it all depends on the driver.

1630
01:00:07,670 --> 01:00:08,838
THE PROBLEM IS THE DRIVING SKILL

1631
01:00:09,672 --> 01:00:10,974
GOLDEN BROWN

1632
01:00:11,040 --> 01:00:11,975
Fried to perfection!

1633
01:00:12,041 --> 01:00:14,010
-It looks good.
-It looks like a frog.

1634
01:00:14,077 --> 01:00:15,812
It's golden brown.
I can't wait until it's done.

1635
01:00:16,179 --> 01:00:17,981
A GOLDEN FROG THAT BRINGS IN RICHES

1636
01:00:18,047 --> 01:00:20,216
It'll be delicious with the onion.

1637
01:00:20,283 --> 01:00:22,085
-Chili oil.
-He throws in the chili oil.

1638
01:00:23,119 --> 01:00:25,855
Good. Very good. That's perfect.

1639
01:00:25,922 --> 01:00:28,024
He even brought excellent tools.

1640
01:00:28,091 --> 01:00:29,525
-You're right.
-Yes.

1641
01:00:29,592 --> 01:00:30,994
Of course. It's the championship.

1642
01:00:31,060 --> 01:00:32,629
This is how
<i>Chef & My Fridge</i> Championship works.

1643
01:00:32,695 --> 01:00:34,530
You have five minutes left.

1644
01:00:34,597 --> 01:00:36,633
Five minutes and thirty seconds.

1645
01:00:36,699 --> 01:00:37,533
Five minutes?

1646
01:00:37,600 --> 01:00:38,735
Is it my turn?

1647
01:00:38,801 --> 01:00:40,303
-Yes.
-Get ready.

1648
01:00:41,537 --> 01:00:43,439
-It's a lemon.
-A lemon.

1649
01:00:43,506 --> 01:00:45,475
That's awesome. Good call with the lemon!

1650
01:00:45,541 --> 01:00:46,643
Lemon.

1651
01:00:46,709 --> 01:00:48,144
-He likes lemons!
-Make it sour.

1652
01:00:48,211 --> 01:00:49,045
-Make it sour.
-Sour?

1653
01:00:49,112 --> 01:00:51,114
Make it tangy.

1654
01:00:51,381 --> 01:00:53,116
PICKLES + SUN-DRIED TOMATO
+CRUSHED GARLIC

1655
01:00:53,182 --> 01:00:54,884
-Lemon!
-They're both using lemons.

1656
01:00:54,951 --> 01:00:56,386
Steal his lemons!

1657
01:00:56,452 --> 01:00:57,587
Excellent job.

1658
01:00:58,321 --> 01:00:59,989
She juiced the lemon in there.

1659
01:01:00,056 --> 01:01:02,258
5. CHOP PICKLES AND SUN-DRIED TOMATOES,
AND ADD GARLIC, LEMON JUICE, PEPPER

1660
01:01:02,692 --> 01:01:04,060
POONG USES LEMON JUICE TOO!

1661
01:01:04,127 --> 01:01:04,994
SLIPS

1662
01:01:05,061 --> 01:01:06,429
He's juicing the lemon.

1663
01:01:06,496 --> 01:01:07,930
Oh, for the sauce?

1664
01:01:07,997 --> 01:01:09,032
Lemon juice.

1665
01:01:09,098 --> 01:01:10,400
You're rather rough today.

1666
01:01:10,466 --> 01:01:11,300
HOW COOL

1667
01:01:11,367 --> 01:01:13,202
He loves the sour taste,
so you should use a lot.

1668
01:01:13,269 --> 01:01:14,470
Very sour.

1669
01:01:14,537 --> 01:01:15,538
Five minutes left.

1670
01:01:15,605 --> 01:01:16,773
Five minutes left.

1671
01:01:16,839 --> 01:01:19,842
Please report from the kitchen,
Jung-hwan and Chef Nam-no!

1672
01:01:19,909 --> 01:01:21,377
I've always wanted to do this.

1673
01:01:22,545 --> 01:01:23,379
How cute.

1674
01:01:23,946 --> 01:01:26,049
Is this well-cooked?

1675
01:01:26,115 --> 01:01:27,283
-I think so.
-It is?

1676
01:01:27,350 --> 01:01:28,785
-Ketchup.
-Ketchup?

1677
01:01:28,851 --> 01:01:30,920
Chili oil, ketchup, and chicken stock.

1678
01:01:30,987 --> 01:01:32,422
Chicken stock.

1679
01:01:33,656 --> 01:01:35,558
-What can we try?
-Hang on.

1680
01:01:35,625 --> 01:01:37,493
-I have this sauce.
-Yes, the sauce.

1681
01:01:37,560 --> 01:01:39,262
-Try the sauce.
-The sauce.

1682
01:01:39,328 --> 01:01:42,665
HER MAYO SAUCE IS UP FOR THE INTERIM CHECK

1683
01:01:42,732 --> 01:01:44,767
-Tell us, Nam-no!
-What do you think?

1684
01:01:44,834 --> 01:01:48,037
You're so eager to win, aren't you?
That sauce is amazing.

1685
01:01:48,104 --> 01:01:50,006
That's not how you do it, Nam-no!

1686
01:01:50,073 --> 01:01:51,541
I'M SUPPOSED TO ASK YOU FIRST!

1687
01:01:51,607 --> 01:01:53,109
Don't you find everything good?

1688
01:01:53,176 --> 01:01:55,445
-No, I'm serious.
-Really? Unbiased?

1689
01:01:55,511 --> 01:01:57,447
-Is this the sauce?
-Yes.

1690
01:01:57,513 --> 01:01:59,348
Onion and chili oil.

1691
01:01:59,415 --> 01:02:01,250
-That's hot.
-Yes.

1692
01:02:01,317 --> 01:02:03,920
-Why don't you try his sauce?
-The smoky flavor.

1693
01:02:04,587 --> 01:02:07,256
I'LL DESTROY EUN-YEONG
AND MAKE MY WAY TO HO-YOUNG!

1694
01:02:07,323 --> 01:02:08,558
Four minutes left.

1695
01:02:08,624 --> 01:02:09,959
-Oh no.
-That looks good.

1696
01:02:10,026 --> 01:02:11,060
This is Poong's sauce.

1697
01:02:11,127 --> 01:02:14,163
Please try both sauces and compare them.

1698
01:02:14,230 --> 01:02:17,233
-Yes, Nam-no.
-So?

1699
01:02:17,300 --> 01:02:19,402
Will it make you crave beer?

1700
01:02:20,636 --> 01:02:22,672
Which sauce will go better with beer?

1701
01:02:23,973 --> 01:02:25,441
What is it? Why is he laughing?

1702
01:02:27,043 --> 01:02:29,278
-This will be his last round.
-His last round?

1703
01:02:29,345 --> 01:02:30,680
No! It's his last round?

1704
01:02:30,747 --> 01:02:31,581
IT'S NOT

1705
01:02:31,647 --> 01:02:33,483
I think Eun-yeong will make it.

1706
01:02:33,549 --> 01:02:36,919
-Is Eun-yeong's sauce better?
-That was the verdict after the sauces.

1707
01:02:36,986 --> 01:02:37,887
Eun-yeong's sauce is better.

1708
01:02:37,954 --> 01:02:39,522
I need Poong to advance.

1709
01:02:39,589 --> 01:02:40,423
SOY SAUCE

1710
01:02:40,490 --> 01:02:43,493
He just put something into the sauce.

1711
01:02:43,559 --> 01:02:46,996
-Soy sauce.
-You'll win if you don't make a mistake.

1712
01:02:47,063 --> 01:02:48,531
THE PAR-FRIED CUBE STEAK!

1713
01:02:48,598 --> 01:02:49,499
-Can I try it?
-Yes.

1714
01:02:49,565 --> 01:02:51,334
The tenderloin!

1715
01:02:51,400 --> 01:02:54,737
-I'm worried about Poong.
-Will the tenderloin make you crave beer?

1716
01:02:54,804 --> 01:02:55,938
It's so good.

1717
01:02:56,005 --> 01:02:57,774
I knew you'd come through, Eun-yeong.

1718
01:02:57,840 --> 01:02:59,575
The tenderloin itself is cooked perfectly.

1719
01:02:59,642 --> 01:03:01,911
She's now stir-frying those
with the sauce.

1720
01:03:01,978 --> 01:03:03,079
-What is that?
-It's good.

1721
01:03:03,146 --> 01:03:05,181
Poong, you need to step up your game.

1722
01:03:05,248 --> 01:03:07,683
ONE MORE DEEP-FRIED NAPA CABBAGE

1723
01:03:07,917 --> 01:03:09,318
I'M THE HERO OF THIS SHOW!

1724
01:03:09,385 --> 01:03:11,854
Is he making a new sauce?

1725
01:03:11,921 --> 01:03:13,089
What's that with the cream?

1726
01:03:13,156 --> 01:03:14,924
-Minced garlic.
-Minced garlic.

1727
01:03:14,991 --> 01:03:17,059
-He added garlic?
-Raw garlic?

1728
01:03:17,126 --> 01:03:20,596
-Can you add garlic to cream?
-I think he'll combine the two.

1729
01:03:20,663 --> 01:03:21,731
Will he mix these?

1730
01:03:21,798 --> 01:03:23,866
-I won't.
-He won't.

1731
01:03:23,933 --> 01:03:25,735
-He won't mix the sauce?
-I think he's making

1732
01:03:25,802 --> 01:03:27,436
something like sour cream.

1733
01:03:27,503 --> 01:03:30,139
It looks like ranch.

1734
01:03:30,206 --> 01:03:32,375
He'll serve different kinds of dips.

1735
01:03:32,441 --> 01:03:34,777
-I think it's burning.
-It's burnt!

1736
01:03:34,844 --> 01:03:36,445
MY NAPA CABBAGE!

1737
01:03:36,512 --> 01:03:38,080
The napa cabbage!

1738
01:03:38,147 --> 01:03:41,017
-What happened to the napa cabbage?
-It's an emergency.

1739
01:03:41,083 --> 01:03:43,419
You can't eat that.

1740
01:03:43,486 --> 01:03:45,888
-It turned into asphalt. It's burnt!
-I'll just serve this.

1741
01:03:47,323 --> 01:03:48,524
EUN-YEONG BEGINS PLATING!

1742
01:03:48,591 --> 01:03:49,926
THE DEEP-FRIED BREAD

1743
01:03:49,992 --> 01:03:51,160
TENDERLOIN STIR-FRIED
IN HER PERSONAL SAUCE

1744
01:03:51,227 --> 01:03:52,862
TOMATO PICKLE

1745
01:03:55,298 --> 01:03:56,833
-Can I try this?
-A minute and thirty seconds!

1746
01:03:57,166 --> 01:03:59,468
THE MOTH TO A FLAME
ISN'T HERE TO FOOL AROUND TODAY

1747
01:03:59,735 --> 01:04:00,837
MAIN, SIDE DISH

1748
01:04:01,337 --> 01:04:02,171
DEEP-FRIED BREAD

1749
01:04:03,239 --> 01:04:05,942
Can you try the cream sauce?
The one that looks like ranch.

1750
01:04:06,008 --> 01:04:07,777
The cream sauce.

1751
01:04:07,844 --> 01:04:10,947
-He put a lot of work into it.
-The cream sauce.

1752
01:04:12,481 --> 01:04:14,050
How many bottles of beer can he have?

1753
01:04:14,116 --> 01:04:16,118
How many bottles of beer can he have?

1754
01:04:16,185 --> 01:04:18,087
-Eun-yeong finishes!
-What? That was fast.

1755
01:04:18,154 --> 01:04:19,488
Park Eun-yeong is done!

1756
01:04:20,022 --> 01:04:24,160
It's really sour, and it goes very well
with the perilla leaves. It's really good.

1757
01:04:24,227 --> 01:04:25,928
It seems like Poong will serve two sauces.

1758
01:04:25,995 --> 01:04:27,830
Yes, Poong will serve two sauces.

1759
01:04:27,897 --> 01:04:29,732
-Let me try this once again.
-Go ahead.

1760
01:04:29,799 --> 01:04:31,734
He tries the sauce again
after it's boiled down.

1761
01:04:31,801 --> 01:04:34,337
-Do you want to have it with beer?
-Many different sauces.

1762
01:04:35,838 --> 01:04:37,506
-He figured it out.
-He figured it out?

1763
01:04:37,573 --> 01:04:38,407
It was the soy sauce.

1764
01:04:39,141 --> 01:04:41,010
-It's like chili sauce.
-Chili sauce.

1765
01:04:41,077 --> 01:04:44,547
-It's like chili shrimp.
-I get it. Shrimp in chili sauce.

1766
01:04:44,614 --> 01:04:45,982
Wait.

1767
01:04:46,048 --> 01:04:46,883
HAHAHAHAHA

1768
01:04:47,283 --> 01:04:48,651
WHAT IS IT?

1769
01:04:48,718 --> 01:04:51,020
This one looks too burnt.

1770
01:04:51,087 --> 01:04:53,022
This is too burnt.

1771
01:04:54,190 --> 01:04:56,092
IS IT CHARCOAL?

1772
01:04:58,361 --> 01:04:59,829
DEEPLY DISAPPOINTED

1773
01:04:59,896 --> 01:05:02,999
-It looks like asphalt.
-Fifty seconds.

1774
01:05:03,065 --> 01:05:04,834
Wait, this has to be a joke.

1775
01:05:05,368 --> 01:05:06,702
It came from a pit of fire.

1776
01:05:06,769 --> 01:05:08,204
No, I'm not using that one!

1777
01:05:08,271 --> 01:05:10,506
-There's another one he made earlier.
-There is?

1778
01:05:10,573 --> 01:05:13,075
-Poong continues, and Eun-yeong is done.
-Sour cream.

1779
01:05:13,142 --> 01:05:14,644
He's finishing up.

1780
01:05:14,710 --> 01:05:15,711
ONION KETCHUP SAUCE

1781
01:05:15,778 --> 01:05:16,879
Those are dips?

1782
01:05:16,946 --> 01:05:18,247
-Hurry up.
-You need to plate it.

1783
01:05:18,314 --> 01:05:22,084
-Master Poong, you have 15 seconds!
-Hurry up.

1784
01:05:22,151 --> 01:05:24,520
Where's the cutlet?
The shrimp and napa cabbage cutlet?

1785
01:05:24,587 --> 01:05:25,788
Master Poong!

1786
01:05:26,355 --> 01:05:28,257
THE SUCCESSFUL ONE FROM EARLIER

1787
01:05:28,324 --> 01:05:31,694
-The other one is completely charred.
-Eight, seven,

1788
01:05:31,761 --> 01:05:36,399
-six, five, four, three,
-Six, five, four, three…

1789
01:05:36,465 --> 01:05:38,901
-two, one.
-It has to remain crunchy.

1790
01:05:38,968 --> 01:05:40,770
-The end.
-It's over.

1791
01:05:40,836 --> 01:05:42,672
-Webtoon Artist Poong finishes too!
-He's done!

1792
01:05:42,738 --> 01:05:44,340
It's like Taiwanese fried chicken.

1793
01:05:44,407 --> 01:05:45,875
It looks good.

1794
01:05:45,942 --> 01:05:47,743
Poong, you're something.

1795
01:05:47,810 --> 01:05:49,211
-It's good.
-It looks good.

1796
01:05:49,278 --> 01:05:51,814
My gosh. I can't believe
they made all this in time.

1797
01:05:51,881 --> 01:05:53,282
It looks like a pork cutlet.

1798
01:05:53,883 --> 01:05:56,752
It's my first time trying
deep-fried napa cabbage.

1799
01:05:56,819 --> 01:06:01,624
We now have both beer snacks
made just for Won-hun.

1800
01:06:01,691 --> 01:06:04,560
-Please try Chef Eun-yeong's dish first.
-I'm curious.

1801
01:06:04,627 --> 01:06:06,295
Can you do this once more?

1802
01:06:08,564 --> 01:06:11,667
TENDERLOIN CUBE STEAK
WITH HER PERSONAL SAUCE

1803
01:06:12,468 --> 01:06:14,804
WITH A SIDE OF DEEP-FRIED PASTRY

1804
01:06:14,870 --> 01:06:17,106
AND TOMATO PICKLE

1805
01:06:17,807 --> 01:06:21,143
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
KIM POONG? SO RELIEVED!

1806
01:06:21,210 --> 01:06:23,312
-I must pour him a drink.
-Yes, it's a beer snack.

1807
01:06:23,379 --> 01:06:24,280
Thank you.

1808
01:06:24,347 --> 01:06:26,916
-The dishes are served with beer.
-Thank you.

1809
01:06:26,983 --> 01:06:30,152
-Pour a nice glass, will you?
-Yes, with a perfect amount of froth.

1810
01:06:30,219 --> 01:06:32,655
Don't make too much froth.

1811
01:06:32,722 --> 01:06:34,557
-That's important.
-It looks perfect.

1812
01:06:34,623 --> 01:06:35,458
This is perfection.

1813
01:06:35,524 --> 01:06:36,359
PERFECT

1814
01:06:36,425 --> 01:06:37,593
-It's perfect.
-Stop right there.

1815
01:06:38,260 --> 01:06:39,595
-Please.
-Thank you.

1816
01:06:39,662 --> 01:06:41,597
How should I eat this?

1817
01:06:41,664 --> 01:06:44,433
Grab the deep-fried bread
and top it with some pickles.

1818
01:06:44,500 --> 01:06:46,669
Then, put some cube steak on it
and eat everything together.

1819
01:06:46,736 --> 01:06:47,870
I see. Like that?

1820
01:06:47,937 --> 01:06:50,139
-That has to be good.
-Yes, no questions asked.

1821
01:06:50,706 --> 01:06:51,974
-Gosh.
-It's that sauce.

1822
01:06:52,041 --> 01:06:53,642
This must be phenomenal.

1823
01:06:54,210 --> 01:06:57,413
-That'll be game over with beer.
-It already looks so good.

1824
01:06:57,480 --> 01:06:59,181
I mean, look at it.

1825
01:06:59,248 --> 01:07:01,584
-It looks so good.
-It's a beer snack.

1826
01:07:02,151 --> 01:07:03,252
That's the bite of the year.

1827
01:07:03,319 --> 01:07:05,454
CHOSEN BY NAM-NO
THE BITE OF THE YEAR

1828
01:07:05,521 --> 01:07:06,989
That crunch.

1829
01:07:07,056 --> 01:07:08,958
You can hear the crunch.

1830
01:07:09,592 --> 01:07:11,527
GOSH, PLEASE…

1831
01:07:11,594 --> 01:07:12,661
PUT ONE IN MY MOUTH…

1832
01:07:12,728 --> 01:07:14,463
I can hear the crunchiness.

1833
01:07:14,530 --> 01:07:16,665
It's a mix of everything that's delicious.

1834
01:07:17,433 --> 01:07:19,235
AN AUTOMATIC SMILE

1835
01:07:19,835 --> 01:07:21,570
-It must be good.
-Gosh.

1836
01:07:23,639 --> 01:07:24,707
I'm so moved.

1837
01:07:24,774 --> 01:07:26,075
-Really?
-I see.

1838
01:07:26,142 --> 01:07:28,978
Tenderloin is the most tender cut, right?

1839
01:07:29,045 --> 01:07:30,880
The tenderness is maintained perfectly,

1840
01:07:30,946 --> 01:07:31,814
and I have never had…

1841
01:07:31,881 --> 01:07:32,715
TOMATO PICKLE

1842
01:07:32,782 --> 01:07:34,450
…anything that tastes like these pickles.

1843
01:07:35,451 --> 01:07:37,753
It mitigates the greasiness.

1844
01:07:37,820 --> 01:07:41,023
<i>-Pickles and tomatoes, right?</i>
<i>-You're right.</i>

1845
01:07:41,090 --> 01:07:43,826
I love the combination of the two.

1846
01:07:43,893 --> 01:07:45,761
And as for the texture of the bread,

1847
01:07:45,828 --> 01:07:48,631
I've never had bread this crunchy before.

1848
01:07:48,697 --> 01:07:50,332
Didn't it absorb too much oil?

1849
01:07:50,900 --> 01:07:52,068
Not at all.

1850
01:07:52,134 --> 01:07:53,803
-It's absolutely delicious.
-I knew it.

1851
01:07:53,869 --> 01:07:55,704
-It didn't absorb oil?
-That's my big sis.

1852
01:07:55,771 --> 01:07:58,474
I've never had anything
this delicious in my life.

1853
01:07:58,541 --> 01:08:00,176
-That's crazy.
-I mean it.

1854
01:08:00,242 --> 01:08:01,777
He'll try some beer too.

1855
01:08:03,245 --> 01:08:04,647
This needs to hit right.

1856
01:08:06,382 --> 01:08:07,883
-He's chugging.
-Gosh.

1857
01:08:07,950 --> 01:08:09,852
AHH

1858
01:08:10,553 --> 01:08:11,387
He's craving more.

1859
01:08:11,454 --> 01:08:12,421
This is the best.

1860
01:08:13,022 --> 01:08:14,924
He said it's the best.

1861
01:08:14,990 --> 01:08:17,960
He took a bite of a rich dish
and washed it down with beer.

1862
01:08:18,027 --> 01:08:19,528
I want to try some.

1863
01:08:19,595 --> 01:08:20,663
I personally

1864
01:08:21,464 --> 01:08:22,998
like this one much more
than the stone pot rice.

1865
01:08:23,899 --> 01:08:25,434
-It's even better than the stone pot rice?
-Hang on.

1866
01:08:25,501 --> 01:08:26,969
-It's an emergency.
-Poong fought well.

1867
01:08:27,603 --> 01:08:28,838
UGH…

1868
01:08:28,904 --> 01:08:30,272
-You did well.
-That sauce was so good.

1869
01:08:32,308 --> 01:08:35,644
She deep-fried the bread
and told him to top it with meat.

1870
01:08:36,245 --> 01:08:38,314
1,000% IMMERSED

1871
01:08:38,380 --> 01:08:40,349
Did you also use ketchup?

1872
01:08:40,416 --> 01:08:44,253
<i>I used mayo, mustard, wasabi,</i>
<i>and maple syrup.</i>

1873
01:08:44,320 --> 01:08:47,656
She can probably release this sauce
as a product.

1874
01:08:48,591 --> 01:08:51,660
-It would go well with any kind of food.
-As expected.

1875
01:08:51,727 --> 01:08:53,028
-It's so good.
-Another sip.

1876
01:08:53,095 --> 01:08:55,664
She should release it and call it
"Eun-yeong's Personal Sauce."

1877
01:08:55,731 --> 01:08:58,000
-Personal Sauce.
-It sounds like a brand.

1878
01:08:59,235 --> 01:09:01,937
Won-hun keeps drinking more beer.

1879
01:09:02,738 --> 01:09:04,173
BOTTOMS UP

1880
01:09:04,240 --> 01:09:05,975
-It must make him crave more beer.
-More and more.

1881
01:09:06,041 --> 01:09:07,409
Was that a whole can?

1882
01:09:08,444 --> 01:09:11,680
-No one can hate this.
-No. He's right. It's impossible.

1883
01:09:11,747 --> 01:09:14,083
It's something everyone would love.

1884
01:09:14,149 --> 01:09:15,451
A taste everyone would like.

1885
01:09:15,518 --> 01:09:16,552
Thank you so much.

1886
01:09:16,619 --> 01:09:18,387
All right, then.

1887
01:09:18,454 --> 01:09:21,423
Next, please try
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong's dish.

1888
01:09:21,490 --> 01:09:23,025
<i>Master Napa Cabbage, Master Poong.</i>

1889
01:09:23,092 --> 01:09:24,493
NAPA CABBAGE CUTLET WITH SHRIMP

1890
01:09:25,394 --> 01:09:29,798
ENJOY IT WITH TWO SAUCES,
LEMON CREAM AND ONION KETCHUP

1891
01:09:32,101 --> 01:09:35,237
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S
MASTER NAPA CABBAGE, MASTER POONG

1892
01:09:35,304 --> 01:09:36,639
Can he win against that though?

1893
01:09:37,239 --> 01:09:40,142
I tried his sauces,
and they were really good.

1894
01:09:40,209 --> 01:09:45,014
You said you deep-fried napa cabbage
with shrimp,

1895
01:09:45,080 --> 01:09:47,383
and I can't imagine
what that would be like.

1896
01:09:47,449 --> 01:09:49,218
I've never had anything like this.

1897
01:09:49,885 --> 01:09:50,719
My gosh.

1898
01:09:50,786 --> 01:09:53,889
The cross-section shows
that the inside is full of shrimp.

1899
01:09:53,956 --> 01:09:55,391
-It looks good.
-You're right.

1900
01:09:55,958 --> 01:09:57,793
DIPPING IN THE LEMON CREAM SAUCE

1901
01:09:57,860 --> 01:09:59,161
-That looks good.
-It does.

1902
01:09:59,228 --> 01:10:02,364
That's made with napa cabbage.
It's not a pork cutlet, but napa cabbage.

1903
01:10:02,431 --> 01:10:04,066
Napa cabbage with shrimp.

1904
01:10:05,067 --> 01:10:06,602
What's it like?

1905
01:10:08,237 --> 01:10:09,071
Wow.

1906
01:10:10,039 --> 01:10:11,240
DID HE SUCCEED AGAIN?

1907
01:10:11,307 --> 01:10:13,342
It's such an uncanny combination.

1908
01:10:14,276 --> 01:10:15,611
Is it uncanny?

1909
01:10:15,678 --> 01:10:17,780
I wouldn't say it's good,
but it's very uncanny.

1910
01:10:17,846 --> 01:10:20,382
-It should be good though.
-It should be.

1911
01:10:20,449 --> 01:10:22,251
Let me try it one more time.

1912
01:10:22,318 --> 01:10:23,252
Did he try too hard?

1913
01:10:23,319 --> 01:10:25,254
-Is it hard to say?
-It's…

1914
01:10:25,321 --> 01:10:27,389
-What's this sauce?
-I mean, it's hard to say.

1915
01:10:27,456 --> 01:10:30,226
I mixed the cooking cream you had

1916
01:10:30,292 --> 01:10:32,861
with lots of lemon juice,
a bit of minced garlic…

1917
01:10:32,928 --> 01:10:35,231
-Perilla leaves.
-…and perilla leaves.

1918
01:10:35,297 --> 01:10:37,333
-You said you liked the sourness of lemon.
-I did.

1919
01:10:37,399 --> 01:10:40,135
So I made a tangier version of sour cream.

1920
01:10:41,103 --> 01:10:43,205
I think I understand
what you were going for.

1921
01:10:43,272 --> 01:10:46,041
How can I put this?
I keep going back for more.

1922
01:10:46,108 --> 01:10:47,476
-It's refreshing.
-You're right.

1923
01:10:47,543 --> 01:10:50,779
-Try the red sauce for another flavor.
-The red sauce.

1924
01:10:50,846 --> 01:10:51,947
It'll taste different.

1925
01:10:52,014 --> 01:10:53,349
-It could be better.
-Dip it in.

1926
01:10:53,415 --> 01:10:56,118
That sauce is delicious enough
to turn everything around.

1927
01:10:56,685 --> 01:10:58,387
What's this one like?

1928
01:10:58,454 --> 01:10:59,455
HOW'S THE SECOND SAUCE?

1929
01:11:02,091 --> 01:11:03,592
This sauce is much better.

1930
01:11:04,193 --> 01:11:07,096
When he minced the shrimp,

1931
01:11:07,162 --> 01:11:09,265
<i>I thought he minced them finely.</i>

1932
01:11:09,331 --> 01:11:10,399
But now that I'm trying it,

1933
01:11:10,466 --> 01:11:12,935
I can still feel the firm texture
on the inside.

1934
01:11:13,002 --> 01:11:14,603
And the napa cabbage is still crunchy.

1935
01:11:15,304 --> 01:11:17,606
But because they were deep-fried,

1936
01:11:17,673 --> 01:11:20,876
the sauce balances out the greasiness.

1937
01:11:20,943 --> 01:11:24,747
-It's a wonderful beer snack.
-He delivers.

1938
01:11:25,281 --> 01:11:26,615
AN IMMEDIATE SIP OF BEER

1939
01:11:26,682 --> 01:11:29,618
-He drinks more beer.
-That looks good.

1940
01:11:29,685 --> 01:11:31,954
These dishes all look insane.

1941
01:11:32,021 --> 01:11:33,055
Everything looks good today.

1942
01:11:33,122 --> 01:11:34,390
I'll settle for some soda.

1943
01:11:35,357 --> 01:11:36,725
It's good.

1944
01:11:36,792 --> 01:11:38,427
But because my order today was,

1945
01:11:38,494 --> 01:11:40,729
"I Mean, I Want to Eat It With Beer,"

1946
01:11:40,796 --> 01:11:43,365
so I'll choose the dish
that goes better with beer.

1947
01:11:43,432 --> 01:11:45,200
-I see.
-There might be a twist.

1948
01:11:45,267 --> 01:11:48,270
All right. Su-ji, you should try some too.

1949
01:11:48,337 --> 01:11:50,539
Please give her some beer snacks.

1950
01:11:50,606 --> 01:11:52,641
-It's really good. I mean it.
-Should I give her these?

1951
01:11:53,042 --> 01:11:55,344
ONE LAST BITE

1952
01:11:56,345 --> 01:11:57,246
It's so good.

1953
01:11:57,313 --> 01:12:01,050
-Please try Chef Eun-yeong's dish first.
-The cube steak.

1954
01:12:01,116 --> 01:12:03,319
-Kim Poong? So Relieved.
-Kim Poong? So Relieved?

1955
01:12:03,385 --> 01:12:04,320
Oh wow.

1956
01:12:07,122 --> 01:12:08,757
FINISHES IT IN ONE BITE

1957
01:12:09,325 --> 01:12:11,126
Gosh, the meat is so tender.

1958
01:12:12,127 --> 01:12:13,395
It's so good.

1959
01:12:13,462 --> 01:12:15,264
DDU-JI'S CAM

1960
01:12:15,331 --> 01:12:16,198
CRUNCH

1961
01:12:16,265 --> 01:12:17,366
It's a perfect beer snack.

1962
01:12:18,500 --> 01:12:19,935
SAVORING

1963
01:12:20,002 --> 01:12:23,138
As he mentioned before,
the sauce has a great balance.

1964
01:12:23,205 --> 01:12:26,041
It tastes rich with a bit of sourness.

1965
01:12:26,108 --> 01:12:27,776
I love it. I like the texture too.

1966
01:12:27,843 --> 01:12:29,545
It'll have a good balance with beer--

1967
01:12:29,611 --> 01:12:30,813
You're done.

1968
01:12:31,246 --> 01:12:32,414
CLEAN

1969
01:12:32,481 --> 01:12:35,684
The fact that she served
the deep-fried bread

1970
01:12:35,751 --> 01:12:38,787
makes a statement
that this isn't the main dish,

1971
01:12:38,854 --> 01:12:42,291
-but a snack, so that was significant.
-You're right.

1972
01:12:42,358 --> 01:12:45,361
-Next, Webtoon Artist Poong's dish.
-Okay.

1973
01:12:45,427 --> 01:12:46,762
Master Napa Cabbage, Master Poong.

1974
01:12:46,829 --> 01:12:48,864
-Go ahead.
-We have some here.

1975
01:12:48,931 --> 01:12:51,533
He made two sauces.
Do I begin with the white one?

1976
01:12:51,600 --> 01:12:53,302
Will it go well with napa cabbage?

1977
01:12:54,937 --> 01:12:56,305
This is so good too.

1978
01:12:56,372 --> 01:12:57,740
It's good.

1979
01:12:57,806 --> 01:12:59,875
That sweetness of the napa cabbage
is so savory.

1980
01:12:59,942 --> 01:13:02,511
-It's so good.
-This goes well with beer too.

1981
01:13:02,578 --> 01:13:05,481
I like sour food too,
so it's not too sour for me.

1982
01:13:08,150 --> 01:13:11,920
Poong's red sauce is amazing.

1983
01:13:11,987 --> 01:13:14,857
The white one is rather sour.

1984
01:13:15,424 --> 01:13:17,559
The napa cabbage
maintained its crunchiness.

1985
01:13:17,626 --> 01:13:18,494
MMM

1986
01:13:19,695 --> 01:13:20,529
MMM

1987
01:13:24,867 --> 01:13:25,734
MM-MMM

1988
01:13:26,602 --> 01:13:28,203
How many times are you saying that?

1989
01:13:28,270 --> 01:13:29,605
MMM-ING FOR THE NTH TIME

1990
01:13:29,671 --> 01:13:30,773
-For me…
-Yes?

1991
01:13:30,839 --> 01:13:33,442
…I liked this one, this red sauce.

1992
01:13:33,509 --> 01:13:36,578
It hit the bull's eye of my appetite.

1993
01:13:37,413 --> 01:13:40,649
This is basically a combination
of shrimp and napa cabbage, right?

1994
01:13:40,716 --> 01:13:42,551
It can never make you fat.

1995
01:13:43,118 --> 01:13:43,986
But it was deep-fried.

1996
01:13:44,052 --> 01:13:45,721
-Sorry?
-It was deep-fried.

1997
01:13:45,788 --> 01:13:48,724
So people who are concerned
about their health, like me,

1998
01:13:48,791 --> 01:13:51,326
will appreciate this combo,
napa cabbage and shrimp.

1999
01:13:51,393 --> 01:13:53,429
-It's not too heavy.
-Right.

2000
01:13:53,495 --> 01:13:54,663
And breadcrumbs.

2001
01:13:54,730 --> 01:13:56,598
-It's not meat…
-And oil.

2002
01:13:56,665 --> 01:13:57,966
-…so it's easier on your stomach.
-That's right.

2003
01:13:58,033 --> 01:14:00,402
When I had the tip of the napa cabbage,

2004
01:14:00,469 --> 01:14:04,072
it felt like the crispy outer part
of a napa cabbage <i>jeon</i>,

2005
01:14:04,139 --> 01:14:05,707
but when I had it with the red sauce,

2006
01:14:05,774 --> 01:14:08,944
it changed to Chinese cuisine
and tasted like chili sauce shrimp.

2007
01:14:09,011 --> 01:14:11,180
Lastly, the white sauce
reminded me of tartar sauce,

2008
01:14:11,246 --> 01:14:14,316
-so it was almost like a French dish.
-French?

2009
01:14:14,383 --> 01:14:16,618
It's the entire world in one dish.

2010
01:14:16,685 --> 01:14:18,320
You can taste the entire world.

2011
01:14:18,754 --> 01:14:20,756
AS EXPECTED…

2012
01:14:20,823 --> 01:14:22,958
He's definitely indebted to him.

2013
01:14:23,025 --> 01:14:24,660
He owes him something.

2014
01:14:24,726 --> 01:14:25,828
-Something huge.
-Chef Ho-young?

2015
01:14:25,894 --> 01:14:27,663
If he can pull off
something like this every round,

2016
01:14:27,729 --> 01:14:29,565
he might have a chance
to reach the finals.

2017
01:14:30,365 --> 01:14:32,267
It tasted ominous.

2018
01:14:33,001 --> 01:14:33,836
Ominous taste.

2019
01:14:33,902 --> 01:14:37,306
-It's now time to choose.
-This is hard.

2020
01:14:37,372 --> 01:14:38,540
The moment of truth.

2021
01:14:38,607 --> 01:14:40,409
<i>Press one for Park Eun-yeong.</i>

2022
01:14:41,109 --> 01:14:42,945
<i>Press two for Kim Poong.</i>

2023
01:14:43,612 --> 01:14:44,880
Make your decision

2024
01:14:45,614 --> 01:14:47,349
and press the button to choose

2025
01:14:47,416 --> 01:14:48,350
the winner.

2026
01:14:49,818 --> 01:14:51,019
I can't do this with a sober mind.

2027
01:14:53,322 --> 01:14:54,923
You said you never got drunk.

2028
01:14:54,990 --> 01:14:56,091
CHOKING

2029
01:14:56,658 --> 01:14:57,860
HE'LL BE SOBER ANYWAY

2030
01:14:57,926 --> 01:14:59,895
-I made my decision.
-He picked one.

2031
01:14:59,962 --> 01:15:01,630
Let's find out

2032
01:15:01,697 --> 01:15:04,800
whose hand Won-hun took
and made them the winner.

2033
01:15:04,867 --> 01:15:06,134
Show us!

2034
01:15:07,436 --> 01:15:09,671
I Mean, I Want to Eat It With Beer.

2035
01:15:09,738 --> 01:15:11,006
Was it a bonus round or not?

2036
01:15:11,073 --> 01:15:13,775
Who'll make their way
to round three of the championship?

2037
01:15:13,842 --> 01:15:15,811
Park Eun-yeong versus Kim Poong.

2038
01:15:15,878 --> 01:15:18,514
Eun-yeong has never lost to Poong!

2039
01:15:19,181 --> 01:15:23,385
Poong has never lost a beer snack round!

2040
01:15:23,452 --> 01:15:24,686
Which one of the two

2041
01:15:25,287 --> 01:15:27,489
did Won-hun choose?

2042
01:15:27,556 --> 01:15:30,659
-Who will Ho-young go against?
-I wonder.

2043
01:15:30,726 --> 01:15:32,060
Who is it?

2044
01:15:32,127 --> 01:15:33,462
Show us!

2045
01:15:33,529 --> 01:15:34,496
The beer snack!

2046
01:15:35,464 --> 01:15:36,431
The beer snack!

2047
01:15:37,699 --> 01:15:39,568
Show us! The beer snack!

2048
01:15:39,635 --> 01:15:41,303
PARK EUN-YEONG WINS

2049
01:15:41,370 --> 01:15:42,538
It was Park Eun-yeong!

2050
01:15:43,005 --> 01:15:44,306
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
KIM POONG? SO RELIEVED! WINS

2051
01:15:44,373 --> 01:15:46,775
-You're so cool today!
-Park Eun-yeong advances again!

2052
01:15:46,842 --> 01:15:49,244
-That's my big sis.
-No one can stop her!

2053
01:15:49,311 --> 01:15:51,013
You can win this.

2054
01:15:51,079 --> 01:15:53,615
-She's always tough against Poong.
-I think she'll win.

2055
01:15:53,682 --> 01:15:55,884
I had no choice but to choose her dish.

2056
01:15:56,451 --> 01:15:57,653
The moment I put it in my mouth,

2057
01:15:57,719 --> 01:15:59,555
I wanted some beer right away.

2058
01:16:00,122 --> 01:16:03,525
I really enjoyed the dish

2059
01:16:03,592 --> 01:16:05,861
Chef Poong made for me as well,

2060
01:16:05,928 --> 01:16:08,363
but I have the palate of a kid.

2061
01:16:09,131 --> 01:16:12,768
And I thought Chef Eun-yeong's dish

2062
01:16:12,834 --> 01:16:15,070
-had the flavor everyone could enjoy…
-True.

2063
01:16:15,137 --> 01:16:17,639
-…so I chose her.
-I see.

2064
01:16:17,706 --> 01:16:19,575
Eun-yeong, show us your pose.

2065
01:16:19,942 --> 01:16:20,842
CHUCKLE

2066
01:16:20,909 --> 01:16:23,145
-It's not three strikes, but four strikes.
-It's four strikes now.

2067
01:16:23,211 --> 01:16:25,280
She took Poong down four times.

2068
01:16:25,347 --> 01:16:26,582
Kim Poong, four strikes!

2069
01:16:26,648 --> 01:16:27,950
Her nostrils are flaring.

2070
01:16:28,517 --> 01:16:30,586
Kim Poong, four strikes!

2071
01:16:31,887 --> 01:16:34,022
Kim Poong, four strikes!

2072
01:16:37,025 --> 01:16:38,660
AN ADDICTIVE CELEBRATION

2073
01:16:38,727 --> 01:16:39,728
No one can copy that.

2074
01:16:39,795 --> 01:16:43,165
-He lost.
-Poong can win against anyone,

2075
01:16:43,231 --> 01:16:45,934
but never against Eun-yeong.

2076
01:16:46,001 --> 01:16:48,470
I think I did a fantastic job
making it this far.

2077
01:16:48,537 --> 01:16:49,538
You fought well.

2078
01:16:49,605 --> 01:16:51,173
I'll see you next year.

2079
01:16:52,507 --> 01:16:54,910
HIS DARK DISHES
WILL CONTINUE TO PREVAIL IN 2026

2080
01:16:54,977 --> 01:16:56,144
-You did well too, Poong.
-Indeed.

2081
01:16:56,745 --> 01:17:00,382
That means the next match
is the semifinals.

2082
01:17:00,449 --> 01:17:04,319
Chef Jung Ho-young will go against
Chef Park Eun-yeong!

2083
01:17:05,120 --> 01:17:06,555
It's such a huge match.

2084
01:17:06,622 --> 01:17:08,290
-I'm so looking forward to this.
-I'm suddenly nervous.

2085
01:17:09,224 --> 01:17:11,927
Who will become the best chef of 2025?

2086
01:17:11,994 --> 01:17:13,629
There's a bit of tension.

2087
01:17:13,695 --> 01:17:15,163
Wow, sexy veggie.

2088
01:17:15,497 --> 01:17:17,332
A GUEST WHO GUARANTEES YOU'LL LAUGH

2089
01:17:17,399 --> 01:17:19,034
I really love vegetables.

2090
01:17:19,101 --> 01:17:20,168
When she was on a mono diet,

2091
01:17:20,235 --> 01:17:22,137
she ate 40 cucumbers a day.

2092
01:17:23,338 --> 01:17:25,073
Would you prefer more veggies?

2093
01:17:25,140 --> 01:17:27,142
Please make sure
my dish has more meat then.

2094
01:17:27,542 --> 01:17:28,777
IS SU-JI REALLY A VEGGIE LOVER?

2095
01:17:28,844 --> 01:17:30,712
Who will make it to the finals?

2096
01:17:30,779 --> 01:17:32,147
She's been on fire.

2097
01:17:32,214 --> 01:17:33,949
Will Chef Ho-young slam on her brakes?

2098
01:17:34,016 --> 01:17:36,018
-You're deep-frying too?
-It's the same.

2099
01:17:36,084 --> 01:17:37,052
It's the same recipe.

2100
01:17:37,119 --> 01:17:38,954
But this is my personal creation.

2101
01:17:40,489 --> 01:17:42,858
THE EYES OF TRUTH IS ON

2102
01:17:42,924 --> 01:17:44,860
I may have to begin
a fight against myself.

2103
01:17:45,360 --> 01:17:46,895
THE CLASS OF THE 1ST PLACE

2104
01:17:47,129 --> 01:17:48,030
THE 1ST PLACE DELIVERS

2105
01:17:48,530 --> 01:17:49,931
That's just crazy.

2106
01:17:49,998 --> 01:17:51,033
There's not a lot of time.

2107
01:17:51,266 --> 01:17:52,534
THE CRAZIEST DISHES SAVED FOR THE FINALS

2108
01:17:52,901 --> 01:17:55,137
TUNE IN TO MEET
ALL HER LEGENDARY CHARACTERS

2109
01:17:55,203 --> 01:17:57,072
You scored a win today, kid.

2110
01:17:57,372 --> 01:17:58,540
GIVING REACTIONS LIKE A CHAMPION

2111
01:17:58,607 --> 01:18:00,976
Who's the champion for 2025
here at <i>Chef & My Fridge?</i>

2112
01:18:01,043 --> 01:18:02,678
-Who's the champion?
-Who is it?

2113
01:18:05,647 --> 01:18:07,349
<i>Oh, sexy veggie</i>

2114
01:18:19,361 --> 01:18:24,132
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
